84  #define JSON_DEPRECATED __attribute__((deprecated))

91 // allow to disable exceptions
92 #if (defined(__cpp_exceptions) || defined(__EXCEPTIONS) || defined(_CPPUNWIND)) && not defined(JSON_NOEXCEPTION)
93  #define JSON_THROW(exception) throw exception
94  #define JSON_TRY try
95  #define JSON_CATCH(exception) catch(exception)
96 #else
97  #define JSON_THROW(exception) std::abort()
98  #define JSON_TRY if(true)
99  #define JSON_CATCH(exception) if(false)
100 #endif

102 // manual branch prediction
103 #if defined(__clang__) || defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__GNUG__)
104  #define JSON_LIKELY(x) __builtin_expect(!!(x), 1)
105  #define JSON_UNLIKELY(x) __builtin_expect(!!(x), 0)
106 #else
107  #define JSON_LIKELY(x) x
108  #define JSON_UNLIKELY(x) x
109 #endif

145 class exception : public std::exception
146 {
147  public:
149  virtual const char* what() const noexcept override
150  {
151  return m.what();
152  }
153 
155  const int id;
156 
157  protected:
158  exception(int id_, const char* what_arg)
159  : id(id_), m(what_arg)
160  {}
161 
162  static std::string name(const std::string& ename, int id)
163  {
164  return "[json.exception." + ename + "." + std::to_string(id) + "] ";
165  }
166 
167  private:
169  std::runtime_error m;
170 };
171 
207 class parse_error : public exception
208 {
209  public:
218  static parse_error create(int id, size_t byte_, const std::string& what_arg)
219  {
220  std::string w = exception::name("parse_error", id) + "parse error" +
221  (byte_ != 0 ? (" at " + std::to_string(byte_)) : "") +
222  ": " + what_arg;
223  return parse_error(id, byte_, w.c_str());
224  }
225 
236  const size_t byte;
237 
238  private:
239  parse_error(int id_, size_t byte_, const char* what_arg)
240  : exception(id_, what_arg), byte(byte_)
241  {}
242 };

382 // JSON type enumeration //
384 
409 enum class value_t : uint8_t
410 {
411  null,
412  object,
413  array,
414  string,
415  boolean,
416  number_integer,
417  number_unsigned,
418  number_float,
419  discarded
420 };
421 
431 inline bool operator<(const value_t lhs, const value_t rhs) noexcept
432 {
433  static constexpr std::array<uint8_t, 8> order = {{
434  0, // null
435  3, // object
436  4, // array
437  5, // string
438  1, // boolean
439  2, // integer
440  2, // unsigned
441  2, // float
442  }
443  };
444 
445  // discarded values are not comparable
446  if (lhs == value_t::discarded or rhs == value_t::discarded)
447  {
448  return false;
449  }
450 
451  return order[static_cast<std::size_t>(lhs)] <
452  order[static_cast<std::size_t>(rhs)];
453 }

457 // helpers //
459 
460 // alias templates to reduce boilerplate
461 template<bool B, typename T = void>
462 using enable_if_t = typename std::enable_if<B, T>::type;
463 
464 template<typename T>
465 using uncvref_t = typename std::remove_cv<typename std::remove_reference<T>::type>::type;
466 
467 /*
468 Implementation of two C++17 constructs: conjunction, negation. This is needed
469 to avoid evaluating all the traits in a condition
470 
471 For example: not std::is_same<void, T>::value and has_value_type<T>::value
472 will not compile when T = void (on MSVC at least). Whereas
473 conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, T>>, has_value_type<T>>::value will
474 stop evaluating if negation<...>::value == false
475 
476 Please note that those constructs must be used with caution, since symbols can
477 become very long quickly (which can slow down compilation and cause MSVC
478 internal compiler errors). Only use it when you have to (see example ahead).
479 */
480 template<class...> struct conjunction : std::true_type {};
481 template<class B1> struct conjunction<B1> : B1 {};
482 template<class B1, class... Bn>
483 struct conjunction<B1, Bn...> : std::conditional<bool(B1::value), conjunction<Bn...>, B1>::type {};
484 
485 template<class B> struct negation : std::integral_constant < bool, !B::value > {};
486 
487 // dispatch utility (taken from ranges-v3)
488 template<unsigned N> struct priority_tag : priority_tag < N - 1 > {};
489 template<> struct priority_tag<0> {};
490

496 template<value_t> struct external_constructor;
497 
498 template<>
499 struct external_constructor<value_t::boolean>
500 {
501  template<typename BasicJsonType>
502  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t b) noexcept
503  {
504  j.m_type = value_t::boolean;
505  j.m_value = b;
506  j.assert_invariant();
507  }
508 };
509 
510 template<>
511 struct external_constructor<value_t::string>
512 {
513  template<typename BasicJsonType>
514  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const typename BasicJsonType::string_t& s)
515  {
516  j.m_type = value_t::string;
517  j.m_value = s;
518  j.assert_invariant();
519  }
520 };

527  {
528  j.m_type = value_t::number_float;
529  j.m_value = val;
530  j.assert_invariant();
531  }

546 template<>
547 struct external_constructor<value_t::number_integer>
548 {
549  template<typename BasicJsonType>
550  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t val) noexcept

553  j.m_value = val;

558 template<>
559 struct external_constructor<value_t::array>
560 {
561  template<typename BasicJsonType>
562  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const typename BasicJsonType::array_t& arr)
563  {
564  j.m_type = value_t::array;
565  j.m_value = arr;
566  j.assert_invariant();
567  }
568 
569  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType,
570  enable_if_t<not std::is_same<CompatibleArrayType,
571  typename BasicJsonType::array_t>::value,
572  int> = 0>
573  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const CompatibleArrayType& arr)
574  {
575  using std::begin;
576  using std::end;
577  j.m_type = value_t::array;
578  j.m_value.array = j.template create<typename BasicJsonType::array_t>(begin(arr), end(arr));
579  j.assert_invariant();
580  }
581 
582  template<typename BasicJsonType>
583  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const std::vector<bool>& arr)
584  {
585  j.m_type = value_t::array;
586  j.m_value = value_t::array;
587  j.m_value.array->reserve(arr.size());
588  for (bool x : arr)
589  {
590  j.m_value.array->push_back(x);
591  }
592  j.assert_invariant();
593  }
594 };
595 
596 template<>
597 struct external_constructor<value_t::object>
598 {
599  template<typename BasicJsonType>
600  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& obj)
601  {
602  j.m_type = value_t::object;
603  j.m_value = obj;
604  j.assert_invariant();
605  }
606 
607  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType,
608  enable_if_t<not std::is_same<CompatibleObjectType,
609  typename BasicJsonType::object_t>::value,
610  int> = 0>
611  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const CompatibleObjectType& obj)
612  {
613  using std::begin;
614  using std::end;
615 
616  j.m_type = value_t::object;
617  j.m_value.object = j.template create<typename BasicJsonType::object_t>(begin(obj), end(obj));
618  j.assert_invariant();
619  }
620 };

624 // has_/is_ functions //
626 
637 #define NLOHMANN_JSON_HAS_HELPER(type) \
638  template<typename T> struct has_##type { \
639  private: \
640  template<typename U, typename = typename U::type> \
641  static int detect(U &&); \
642  static void detect(...); \
643  public: \
644  static constexpr bool value = \
645  std::is_integral<decltype(detect(std::declval<T>()))>::value; \
646  }
647 
648 NLOHMANN_JSON_HAS_HELPER(mapped_type);
649 NLOHMANN_JSON_HAS_HELPER(key_type);
650 NLOHMANN_JSON_HAS_HELPER(value_type);
651 NLOHMANN_JSON_HAS_HELPER(iterator);
652 
653 #undef NLOHMANN_JSON_HAS_HELPER
654 
655 
656 template<bool B, class RealType, class CompatibleObjectType>
657 struct is_compatible_object_type_impl : std::false_type {};
658 
659 template<class RealType, class CompatibleObjectType>
660 struct is_compatible_object_type_impl<true, RealType, CompatibleObjectType>
661 {
662  static constexpr auto value =
663  std::is_constructible<typename RealType::key_type,
664  typename CompatibleObjectType::key_type>::value and
665  std::is_constructible<typename RealType::mapped_type,
666  typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value;
667 };
668 
669 template<class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleObjectType>
670 struct is_compatible_object_type
671 {
672  static auto constexpr value = is_compatible_object_type_impl <
673  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleObjectType>>,
674  has_mapped_type<CompatibleObjectType>,
675  has_key_type<CompatibleObjectType>>::value,
676  typename BasicJsonType::object_t, CompatibleObjectType >::value;
677 };
678 
679 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
680 struct is_basic_json_nested_type
681 {
682  static auto constexpr value = std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::iterator>::value or
683  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::const_iterator>::value or
684  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::reverse_iterator>::value or
685  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::const_reverse_iterator>::value or
686  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::json_pointer>::value;
687 };
688 
689 template<class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleArrayType>
690 struct is_compatible_array_type
691 {
692  static auto constexpr value =
693  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleArrayType>>,
694  negation<is_compatible_object_type<
695  BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>>,
696  negation<std::is_constructible<typename BasicJsonType::string_t,
697  CompatibleArrayType>>,
698  negation<is_basic_json_nested_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>>,
699  has_value_type<CompatibleArrayType>,
700  has_iterator<CompatibleArrayType>>::value;
701 };
702 
703 template<bool, typename, typename>
704 struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl : std::false_type {};
705 
706 template<typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
707 struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl<true, RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
708 {
709  // is there an assert somewhere on overflows?
710  using RealLimits = std::numeric_limits<RealIntegerType>;
711  using CompatibleLimits = std::numeric_limits<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>;
712 
713  static constexpr auto value =
714  std::is_constructible<RealIntegerType,
715  CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
716  CompatibleLimits::is_integer and
717  RealLimits::is_signed == CompatibleLimits::is_signed;
718 };
719 
720 template<typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
721 struct is_compatible_integer_type
722 {
723  static constexpr auto value =
724  is_compatible_integer_type_impl <
725  std::is_integral<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
726  not std::is_same<bool, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value,
727  RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType > ::value;
728 };

731 // trait checking if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&, udt&) exists
732 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
733 struct has_from_json
734 {
735  private:
736  // also check the return type of from_json
737  template<typename U, typename = enable_if_t<std::is_same<void, decltype(uncvref_t<U>::from_json(
738  std::declval<BasicJsonType>(), std::declval<T&>()))>::value>>
739  static int detect(U&&);
740  static void detect(...);
741 
742  public:
743  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(
744  detect(std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
745 };
746 
747 // This trait checks if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&) exists
748 // this overload is used for non-default-constructible user-defined-types
749 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
750 struct has_non_default_from_json
751 {
752  private:
753  template <
754  typename U,
755  typename = enable_if_t<std::is_same<
756  T, decltype(uncvref_t<U>::from_json(std::declval<BasicJsonType>()))>::value >>
757  static int detect(U&&);
758  static void detect(...);
759 
760  public:
761  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(detect(
762  std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
763 };
764 
765 // This trait checks if BasicJsonType::json_serializer<T>::to_json exists
766 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
767 struct has_to_json
768 {
769  private:
770  template<typename U, typename = decltype(uncvref_t<U>::to_json(
771  std::declval<BasicJsonType&>(), std::declval<T>()))>
772  static int detect(U&&);
773  static void detect(...);
774 
775  public:
776  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(detect(
777  std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
778 };

859 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, std::size_t N,
860  enable_if_t<not std::is_constructible<
861  typename BasicJsonType::string_t, T (&)[N]>::value,
862  int> = 0>
863 void to_json(BasicJsonType& j, T (&arr)[N])
864 {
865  external_constructor<value_t::array>::construct(j, arr);
866 }

869 // from_json //
871 
872 // overloads for basic_json template parameters
873 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
874  enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
875  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType,
876  typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
877  int> = 0>
878 void get_arithmetic_value(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
879 {
880  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j))
881  {
882  case value_t::number_unsigned:
883  {
884  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(
885  *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
886  break;
887  }
888  case value_t::number_integer:
889  {
890  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(
891  *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
892  break;
893  }
894  case value_t::number_float:
895  {
896  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(
897  *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
898  break;
899  }
900  default:
901  {
902  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + j.type_name()));
903  }
904  }
905 }
906 
907 template<typename BasicJsonType>
908 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t& b)
909 {
910  if (not j.is_boolean())
911  {
912  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be boolean, but is " + j.type_name()));
913  }
914  b = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>();
915 }

917 template<typename BasicJsonType>
918 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::string_t& s)
919 {
920  if (not j.is_string())
921  {
922  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be string, but is " + j.type_name()));
923  }
924  s = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::string_t*>();
925 }

929 {

948 {

951  e = static_cast<EnumType>(val);

954 template<typename BasicJsonType>
955 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::array_t& arr)
956 {
957  if (not j.is_array())
958  {
959  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + j.type_name()));
960  }
961  arr = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::array_t*>();

964 // forward_list doesn't have an insert method
965 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename Allocator,
966  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
967 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::forward_list<T, Allocator>& l)
968 {
969  if (not j.is_array())
970  {
971  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + j.type_name()));
972  }
973 
974  for (auto it = j.rbegin(), end = j.rend(); it != end; ++it)
975  {
976  l.push_front(it->template get<T>());
977  }
978 }
979 
980 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
981 void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<0>)
982 {
983  using std::begin;
984  using std::end;
985 
986  std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(),
987  std::inserter(arr, end(arr)), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
988  {
989  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
990  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
991  return i.template get<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>();
992  });
993 }
994 
995 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
996 auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<1>)
997 -> decltype(
998  arr.reserve(std::declval<typename CompatibleArrayType::size_type>()),
999  void())
1000 {
1001  using std::begin;
1002  using std::end;
1003 
1004  arr.reserve(j.size());
1005  std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(),
1006  std::inserter(arr, end(arr)), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1007  {
1008  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1009  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1010  return i.template get<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>();
1011  });
1012 }
1013 
1014 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType,
1015  enable_if_t<is_compatible_array_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>::value and
1016  std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>::value and
1017  not std::is_same<typename BasicJsonType::array_t, CompatibleArrayType>::value, int> = 0>
1018 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr)
1019 {
1020  if (not j.is_array())
1021  {
1022  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + j.type_name()));
1023  }
1024 
1025  from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<1> {});
1026 }
1027 
1028 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType,
1029  enable_if_t<is_compatible_object_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleObjectType>::value, int> = 0>
1030 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleObjectType& obj)
1031 {
1032  if (not j.is_object())
1033  {
1034  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be object, but is " + j.type_name()));
1035  }
1036 
1037  auto inner_object = j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::object_t*>();
1038  using std::begin;
1039  using std::end;
1040  // we could avoid the assignment, but this might require a for loop, which
1041  // might be less efficient than the container constructor for some
1042  // containers (would it?)
1043  obj = CompatibleObjectType(begin(*inner_object), end(*inner_object));
1044 }
1045 
1046 // overload for arithmetic types, not chosen for basic_json template arguments
1047 // (BooleanType, etc..); note: Is it really necessary to provide explicit
1048 // overloads for boolean_t etc. in case of a custom BooleanType which is not
1049 // an arithmetic type?
1050 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
1051  enable_if_t <
1052  std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
1053  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t>::value and
1054  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t>::value and
1055  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t>::value and
1056  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
1057  int> = 0>
1058 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
1059 {
1060  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j))
1061  {
1062  case value_t::number_unsigned:
1063  {
1064  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
1065  break;
1066  }
1067  case value_t::number_integer:
1068  {
1069  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
1070  break;
1071  }
1072  case value_t::number_float:
1073  {
1074  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
1075  break;
1076  }
1077  case value_t::boolean:
1078  {
1079  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>());
1080  break;
1081  }
1082  default:
1083  {
1084  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + j.type_name()));
1085  }
1086  }
1087 }

1089 struct to_json_fn
1090 {
1091  private:
1092  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1093  auto call(BasicJsonType& j, T&& val, priority_tag<1>) const noexcept(noexcept(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val))))
1094  -> decltype(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val)), void())
1095  {
1096  return to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val));
1097  }
1098 
1099  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1100  void call(BasicJsonType&, T&&, priority_tag<0>) const noexcept
1101  {
1102  static_assert(sizeof(BasicJsonType) == 0,
1103  "could not find to_json() method in T's namespace");
1104  }
1105 
1106  public:
1107  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1108  void operator()(BasicJsonType& j, T&& val) const
1109  noexcept(noexcept(std::declval<to_json_fn>().call(j, std::forward<T>(val), priority_tag<1> {})))
1110  {
1111  return call(j, std::forward<T>(val), priority_tag<1> {});
1112  }
1113 };
1114 
1115 struct from_json_fn
1116 {
1117  private:
1118  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1119  auto call(const BasicJsonType& j, T& val, priority_tag<1>) const
1120  noexcept(noexcept(from_json(j, val)))
1121  -> decltype(from_json(j, val), void())
1122  {
1123  return from_json(j, val);
1124  }
1125 
1126  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1127  void call(const BasicJsonType&, T&, priority_tag<0>) const noexcept
1128  {
1129  static_assert(sizeof(BasicJsonType) == 0,
1130  "could not find from_json() method in T's namespace");
1131  }
1132 
1133  public:
1134  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1135  void operator()(const BasicJsonType& j, T& val) const
1136  noexcept(noexcept(std::declval<from_json_fn>().call(j, val, priority_tag<1> {})))
1137  {
1138  return call(j, val, priority_tag<1> {});
1139  }
1140 };

1559  using object_t = ObjectType<StringType,
1560  basic_json,
1561  std::less<StringType>,
1562  AllocatorType<std::pair<const StringType,
1563  basic_json>>>;

1610

1902 
1903  private:
1904 
1906  template<typename T, typename... Args>
1907  static T* create(Args&& ... args)
1908  {
1909  AllocatorType<T> alloc;
1910  auto deleter = [&](T * object)
1911  {
1912  alloc.deallocate(object, 1);
1913  };
1914  std::unique_ptr<T, decltype(deleter)> object(alloc.allocate(1), deleter);
1915  alloc.construct(object.get(), std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1916  assert(object != nullptr);
1917  return object.release();
1918  }

1923 
1948  union json_value
1949  {
1951  object_t* object;
1953  array_t* array;
1955  string_t* string;
1957  boolean_t boolean;
1959  number_integer_t number_integer;
1961  number_unsigned_t number_unsigned;
1963  number_float_t number_float;
1964 
1966  json_value() = default;
1968  json_value(boolean_t v) noexcept : boolean(v) {}
1970  json_value(number_integer_t v) noexcept : number_integer(v) {}
1972  json_value(number_unsigned_t v) noexcept : number_unsigned(v) {}
1974  json_value(number_float_t v) noexcept : number_float(v) {}
1976  json_value(value_t t)
1977  {
1978  switch (t)
1979  {
1980  case value_t::object:
1981  {
1982  object = create<object_t>();
1983  break;
1984  }
1985 
1986  case value_t::array:
1987  {
1988  array = create<array_t>();
1989  break;
1990  }
1991 
1992  case value_t::string:
1993  {
1994  string = create<string_t>("");
1995  break;
1996  }
1997 
1998  case value_t::boolean:
1999  {
2000  boolean = boolean_t(false);
2001  break;
2002  }
2003 
2004  case value_t::number_integer:
2005  {
2006  number_integer = number_integer_t(0);
2007  break;
2008  }
2009 
2010  case value_t::number_unsigned:
2011  {
2012  number_unsigned = number_unsigned_t(0);
2013  break;
2014  }
2015 
2016  case value_t::number_float:
2017  {
2018  number_float = number_float_t(0.0);
2019  break;
2020  }
2021 
2022  case value_t::null:
2023  {
2024  break;
2025  }
2026 
2027  default:
2028  {
2029  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(t == value_t::null))
2030  {
2031  JSON_THROW(other_error::create(500, "961c151d2e87f2686a955a9be24d316f1362bf21 2.1.1")); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
2032  }
2033  break;
2034  }
2035  }
2036  }
2037 
2039  json_value(const string_t& value)
2040  {
2041  string = create<string_t>(value);
2042  }
2043 
2045  json_value(const object_t& value)
2046  {
2047  object = create<object_t>(value);
2048  }
2049 
2051  json_value(const array_t& value)
2052  {
2053  array = create<array_t>(value);
2054  }
2055  };

2277  template<typename CompatibleType, typename U = detail::uncvref_t<CompatibleType>,
2278  detail::enable_if_t<not std::is_base_of<std::istream, U>::value and
2279  not std::is_same<U, basic_json_t>::value and
2280  not detail::is_basic_json_nested_type<
2281  basic_json_t, U>::value and
2282  detail::has_to_json<basic_json, U>::value,
2283  int> = 0>
2284  basic_json(CompatibleType && val) noexcept(noexcept(JSONSerializer<U>::to_json(
2285  std::declval<basic_json_t&>(), std::forward<CompatibleType>(val))))
2286  {
2287  JSONSerializer<U>::to_json(*this, std::forward<CompatibleType>(val));
2288  assert_invariant();

2290 
2362  basic_json(std::initializer_list<basic_json> init,
2363  bool type_deduction = true,
2364  value_t manual_type = value_t::array)
2365  {
2366  // check if each element is an array with two elements whose first
2367  // element is a string
2368  bool is_an_object = std::all_of(init.begin(), init.end(),
2369  [](const basic_json & element)
2370  {
2371  return element.is_array() and element.size() == 2 and element[0].is_string();
2372  });
2373 
2374  // adjust type if type deduction is not wanted
2375  if (not type_deduction)
2376  {
2377  // if array is wanted, do not create an object though possible
2378  if (manual_type == value_t::array)
2379  {
2380  is_an_object = false;
2381  }
2382 
2383  // if object is wanted but impossible, throw an exception
2384  if (manual_type == value_t::object and not is_an_object)
2385  {
2386  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(301, "cannot create object from initializer list"));
2387  }
2388  }
2389 
2390  if (is_an_object)
2391  {
2392  // the initializer list is a list of pairs -> create object
2393  m_type = value_t::object;
2394  m_value = value_t::object;
2395 
2396  std::for_each(init.begin(), init.end(), [this](const basic_json & element)
2397  {
2398  m_value.object->emplace(*(element[0].m_value.string), element[1]);
2399  });
2400  }
2401  else
2402  {
2403  // the initializer list describes an array -> create array
2404  m_type = value_t::array;
2405  m_value.array = create<array_t>(init);
2406  }
2407 
2408  assert_invariant();
2409  }
2410 
2445  static basic_json array(std::initializer_list<basic_json> init =
2446  std::initializer_list<basic_json>())
2447  {
2448  return basic_json(init, false, value_t::array);
2449  }
2450 
2486  static basic_json object(std::initializer_list<basic_json> init =
2487  std::initializer_list<basic_json>())
2488  {
2489  return basic_json(init, false, value_t::object);
2490  }
2491 
2510  basic_json(size_type cnt, const basic_json& val)
2511  : m_type(value_t::array)
2512  {
2513  m_value.array = create<array_t>(cnt, val);
2514  assert_invariant();
2515  }
2516 
2559  template<class InputIT, typename std::enable_if<
2560  std::is_same<InputIT, typename basic_json_t::iterator>::value or
2561  std::is_same<InputIT, typename basic_json_t::const_iterator>::value, int>::type = 0>
2562  basic_json(InputIT first, InputIT last)
2563  {
2564  assert(first.m_object != nullptr);
2565  assert(last.m_object != nullptr);
2566 
2567  // make sure iterator fits the current value
2568  if (first.m_object != last.m_object)
2569  {
2570  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(201, "iterators are not compatible"));
2571  }
2572 
2573  // copy type from first iterator
2574  m_type = first.m_object->m_type;
2575 
2576  // check if iterator range is complete for primitive values
2577  switch (m_type)
2578  {
2579  case value_t::boolean:
2580  case value_t::number_float:
2581  case value_t::number_integer:
2582  case value_t::number_unsigned:
2583  case value_t::string:
2584  {
2585  if (not first.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin() or not last.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_end())
2586  {
2587  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(204, "iterators out of range"));
2588  }
2589  break;
2590  }
2591 
2592  default:
2593  {
2594  break;
2595  }
2596  }
2597 
2598  switch (m_type)
2599  {
2600  case value_t::number_integer:
2601  {
2602  m_value.number_integer = first.m_object->m_value.number_integer;
2603  break;
2604  }
2605 
2606  case value_t::number_unsigned:
2607  {
2608  m_value.number_unsigned = first.m_object->m_value.number_unsigned;
2609  break;
2610  }
2611 
2612  case value_t::number_float:
2613  {
2614  m_value.number_float = first.m_object->m_value.number_float;
2615  break;
2616  }
2617 
2618  case value_t::boolean:
2619  {
2620  m_value.boolean = first.m_object->m_value.boolean;
2621  break;
2622  }
2623 
2624  case value_t::string:
2625  {
2626  m_value = *first.m_object->m_value.string;
2627  break;
2628  }
2629 
2630  case value_t::object:
2631  {
2632  m_value.object = create<object_t>(first.m_it.object_iterator,
2633  last.m_it.object_iterator);
2634  break;
2635  }
2636 
2637  case value_t::array:
2638  {
2639  m_value.array = create<array_t>(first.m_it.array_iterator,
2640  last.m_it.array_iterator);
2641  break;
2642  }
2643 
2644  default:
2645  {
2646  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(206, "cannot construct with iterators from " +
2647  first.m_object->type_name()));
2648  }
2649  }
2650 
2651  assert_invariant();
2652  }
2653

2658 
2679  basic_json(const basic_json& other)
2680  : m_type(other.m_type)
2681  {
2682  // check of passed value is valid
2683  other.assert_invariant();
2684 
2685  switch (m_type)
2686  {
2687  case value_t::object:
2688  {
2689  m_value = *other.m_value.object;
2690  break;
2691  }
2692 
2693  case value_t::array:
2694  {
2695  m_value = *other.m_value.array;
2696  break;
2697  }
2698 
2699  case value_t::string:
2700  {
2701  m_value = *other.m_value.string;
2702  break;
2703  }
2704 
2705  case value_t::boolean:
2706  {
2707  m_value = other.m_value.boolean;
2708  break;
2709  }
2710 
2711  case value_t::number_integer:
2712  {
2713  m_value = other.m_value.number_integer;
2714  break;
2715  }
2716 
2717  case value_t::number_unsigned:
2718  {
2719  m_value = other.m_value.number_unsigned;
2720  break;
2721  }
2722 
2723  case value_t::number_float:
2724  {
2725  m_value = other.m_value.number_float;
2726  break;
2727  }
2728 
2729  default:
2730  {
2731  break;
2732  }
2733  }
2734 
2735  assert_invariant();
2736  }

2756  basic_json(basic_json&& other) noexcept
2757  : m_type(std::move(other.m_type)),
2758  m_value(std::move(other.m_value))
2759  {
2760  // check that passed value is valid
2761  other.assert_invariant();
2762 
2763  // invalidate payload
2764  other.m_type = value_t::null;
2765  other.m_value = {};
2766 
2767  assert_invariant();
2768  }

2793  reference& operator=(basic_json other) noexcept (
2794  std::is_nothrow_move_constructible<value_t>::value and
2795  std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<value_t>::value and
2796  std::is_nothrow_move_constructible<json_value>::value and
2797  std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<json_value>::value
2798  )
2799  {
2800  // check that passed value is valid
2801  other.assert_invariant();
2802 
2803  using std::swap;
2804  swap(m_type, other.m_type);
2805  swap(m_value, other.m_value);
2806 
2807  assert_invariant();
2808  return *this;
2809  }

2826  ~basic_json()
2827  {
2828  assert_invariant();
2829 
2830  switch (m_type)
2831  {
2832  case value_t::object:
2833  {
2834  AllocatorType<object_t> alloc;
2835  alloc.destroy(m_value.object);
2836  alloc.deallocate(m_value.object, 1);
2837  break;
2838  }
2839 
2840  case value_t::array:
2841  {
2842  AllocatorType<array_t> alloc;
2843  alloc.destroy(m_value.array);
2844  alloc.deallocate(m_value.array, 1);
2845  break;
2846  }
2847 
2848  case value_t::string:
2849  {
2850  AllocatorType<string_t> alloc;
2851  alloc.destroy(m_value.string);
2852  alloc.deallocate(m_value.string, 1);
2853  break;
2854  }
2855 
2856  default:
2857  {
2858  // all other types need no specific destructor
2859  break;
2860  }
2861  }

3385  template<typename ReferenceType, typename ThisType>
3386  static ReferenceType get_ref_impl(ThisType& obj)
3387  {
3388  // helper type
3389  using PointerType = typename std::add_pointer<ReferenceType>::type;
3390 
3391  // delegate the call to get_ptr<>()
3392  auto ptr = obj.template get_ptr<PointerType>();
3393 
3394  if (ptr != nullptr)
3395  {
3396  return *ptr;
3397  }
3398 
3399  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(303, "incompatible ReferenceType for get_ref, actual type is " + obj.type_name()));
3400  }

3475  detail::has_from_json<basic_json_t, ValueType>::value and
3476  not detail::has_non_default_from_json<basic_json_t, ValueType>::value,
3477  int > = 0 >
3478  ValueType get() const noexcept(noexcept(
3479  JSONSerializer<ValueType>::from_json(std::declval<const basic_json_t&>(), std::declval<ValueType&>())))
3480  {

3483  // still need the uncvref

3485  "get() cannot be used with reference types, you might want to use get_ref()");

3487  "types must be DefaultConstructible when used with get()");

3613  std::is_pointer<PointerType>::value, int>::type = 0>

3615  {

3617  using pointee_t = typename std::remove_const<typename
3618  std::remove_pointer<typename
3619  std::remove_const<PointerType>::type>::type>::type;
3620  // make sure the type matches the allowed types
3621  static_assert(
3622  std::is_same<object_t, pointee_t>::value

3624  or std::is_same<string_t, pointee_t>::value
3625  or std::is_same<boolean_t, pointee_t>::value

4004  idx - m_value.array->size() + 1,

4006  }

4009  }
4010

4572  template<class IteratorType, typename std::enable_if<
4573  std::is_same<IteratorType, typename basic_json_t::iterator>::value or
4574  std::is_same<IteratorType, typename basic_json_t::const_iterator>::value, int>::type
4575  = 0>
4576  IteratorType erase(IteratorType pos)
4577  {
4578  // make sure iterator fits the current value
4579  if (this != pos.m_object)
4580  {
4581  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(202, "iterator does not fit current value"));
4582  }
4583 
4584  IteratorType result = end();
4585 
4586  switch (m_type)
4587  {
4588  case value_t::boolean:
4589  case value_t::number_float:
4590  case value_t::number_integer:
4591  case value_t::number_unsigned:
4592  case value_t::string:
4593  {
4594  if (not pos.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin())
4595  {
4596  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(205, "iterator out of range"));
4597  }
4598 
4599  if (is_string())
4600  {
4601  AllocatorType<string_t> alloc;
4602  alloc.destroy(m_value.string);
4603  alloc.deallocate(m_value.string, 1);
4604  m_value.string = nullptr;
4605  }
4606 
4607  m_type = value_t::null;
4608  assert_invariant();
4609  break;
4610  }
4611 
4612  case value_t::object:
4613  {
4614  result.m_it.object_iterator = m_value.object->erase(pos.m_it.object_iterator);
4615  break;
4616  }
4617 
4618  case value_t::array:
4619  {
4620  result.m_it.array_iterator = m_value.array->erase(pos.m_it.array_iterator);
4621  break;
4622  }
4623 
4624  default:
4625  {
4626  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(307, "cannot use erase() with " + type_name()));
4627  }
4628  }
4629 
4630  return result;
4631  }
4632 
4679  template<class IteratorType, typename std::enable_if<
4680  std::is_same<IteratorType, typename basic_json_t::iterator>::value or
4681  std::is_same<IteratorType, typename basic_json_t::const_iterator>::value, int>::type
4682  = 0>
4683  IteratorType erase(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
4684  {
4685  // make sure iterator fits the current value
4686  if (this != first.m_object or this != last.m_object)
4687  {
4688  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(203, "iterators do not fit current value"));
4689  }
4690 
4691  IteratorType result = end();
4692 
4693  switch (m_type)
4694  {
4695  case value_t::boolean:
4696  case value_t::number_float:
4697  case value_t::number_integer:
4698  case value_t::number_unsigned:
4699  case value_t::string:
4700  {
4701  if (not first.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin() or not last.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_end())
4702  {
4703  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(204, "iterators out of range"));
4704  }
4705 
4706  if (is_string())
4707  {
4708  AllocatorType<string_t> alloc;
4709  alloc.destroy(m_value.string);
4710  alloc.deallocate(m_value.string, 1);
4711  m_value.string = nullptr;
4712  }
4713 
4714  m_type = value_t::null;
4715  assert_invariant();
4716  break;
4717  }
4718 
4719  case value_t::object:
4720  {
4721  result.m_it.object_iterator = m_value.object->erase(first.m_it.object_iterator,
4722  last.m_it.object_iterator);
4723  break;
4724  }
4725 
4726  case value_t::array:
4727  {
4728  result.m_it.array_iterator = m_value.array->erase(first.m_it.array_iterator,
4729  last.m_it.array_iterator);
4730  break;
4731  }
4732 
4733  default:
4734  {
4735  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(307, "cannot use erase() with " + type_name()));
4736  }
4737  }
4738 
4739  return result;
4740  }

5768  template<class... Args>
5769  std::pair<iterator, bool> emplace(Args&& ... args)
5770  {
5771  // emplace only works for null objects or arrays
5772  if (not(is_null() or is_object()))
5773  {
5774  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(311, "cannot use emplace() with " + type_name()));
5775  }
5776 
5777  // transform null object into an object
5778  if (is_null())
5779  {
5780  m_type = value_t::object;
5781  m_value = value_t::object;
5782  assert_invariant();
5783  }
5784 
5785  // add element to array (perfect forwarding)
5786  auto res = m_value.object->emplace(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
5787  // create result iterator and set iterator to the result of emplace
5788  auto it = begin();
5789  it.m_it.object_iterator = res.first;
5790 
5791  // return pair of iterator and boolean
5792  return {it, res.second};
5793  }

5883  result.m_it.array_iterator = m_value.array->insert(pos.m_it.array_iterator, cnt, val);

5885  }
5886 
5887  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(309, "cannot use insert() with " + type_name()));
5888  }
5889 
5920  iterator insert(const_iterator pos, const_iterator first, const_iterator last)
5921  {
5922  // insert only works for arrays
5923  if (not is_array())
5924  {
5925  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(309, "cannot use insert() with " + type_name()));
5926  }
5927 
5928  // check if iterator pos fits to this JSON value
5929  if (pos.m_object != this)
5930  {
5931  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(202, "iterator does not fit current value"));
5932  }
5933 
5934  // check if range iterators belong to the same JSON object
5935  if (first.m_object != last.m_object)
5936  {
5937  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(210, "iterators do not fit"));
5938  }
5939 
5940  if (first.m_object == this or last.m_object == this)
5941  {
5942  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(211, "passed iterators may not belong to container"));
5943  }
5944 
5945  // insert to array and return iterator
5946  iterator result(this);
5947  result.m_it.array_iterator = m_value.array->insert(
5948  pos.m_it.array_iterator,
5949  first.m_it.array_iterator,
5950  last.m_it.array_iterator);
5951  return result;
5952  }
5953 
5978  iterator insert(const_iterator pos, std::initializer_list<basic_json> ilist)
5979  {
5980  // insert only works for arrays
5981  if (not is_array())
5982  {
5983  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(309, "cannot use insert() with " + type_name()));
5984  }
5985 
5986  // check if iterator pos fits to this JSON value
5987  if (pos.m_object != this)
5988  {
5989  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(202, "iterator does not fit current value"));
5990  }
5991 
5992  // insert to array and return iterator
5993  iterator result(this);
5994  result.m_it.array_iterator = m_value.array->insert(pos.m_it.array_iterator, ilist);
5995  return result;
5996  }
5997 
6021  void insert(const_iterator first, const_iterator last)
6022  {
6023  // insert only works for objects
6024  if (not is_object())
6025  {
6026  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(309, "cannot use insert() with " + type_name()));
6027  }
6028 
6029  // check if range iterators belong to the same JSON object
6030  if (first.m_object != last.m_object)
6031  {
6032  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(210, "iterators do not fit"));
6033  }
6034 
6035  // passed iterators must belong to objects
6036  if (not first.m_object->is_object() or not first.m_object->is_object())
6037  {
6038  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(202, "iterators first and last must point to objects"));
6039  }
6040 
6041  m_value.object->insert(first.m_it.object_iterator, last.m_it.object_iterator);
6042  }

6070  assert_invariant();

6209  friend bool operator==(const_reference lhs, const_reference rhs) noexcept
6210  {
6211  const auto lhs_type = lhs.type();
6212  const auto rhs_type = rhs.type();
6213 
6214  if (lhs_type == rhs_type)
6215  {
6216  switch (lhs_type)
6217  {
6218  case value_t::array:
6219  {
6220  return *lhs.m_value.array == *rhs.m_value.array;
6221  }
6222  case value_t::object:
6223  {
6224  return *lhs.m_value.object == *rhs.m_value.object;
6225  }
6226  case value_t::null:
6227  {
6228  return true;
6229  }
6230  case value_t::string:
6231  {
6232  return *lhs.m_value.string == *rhs.m_value.string;
6233  }
6234  case value_t::boolean:
6235  {
6236  return lhs.m_value.boolean == rhs.m_value.boolean;
6237  }
6238  case value_t::number_integer:
6239  {
6240  return lhs.m_value.number_integer == rhs.m_value.number_integer;
6241  }
6242  case value_t::number_unsigned:
6243  {
6244  return lhs.m_value.number_unsigned == rhs.m_value.number_unsigned;
6245  }
6246  case value_t::number_float:
6247  {
6248  return lhs.m_value.number_float == rhs.m_value.number_float;
6249  }
6250  default:
6251  {
6252  return false;
6253  }
6254  }
6255  }
6256  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer and rhs_type == value_t::number_float)
6257  {
6258  return static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_integer) == rhs.m_value.number_float;
6259  }
6260  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float and rhs_type == value_t::number_integer)
6261  {
6262  return lhs.m_value.number_float == static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_integer);
6263  }
6264  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned and rhs_type == value_t::number_float)
6265  {
6266  return static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) == rhs.m_value.number_float;
6267  }
6268  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float and rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned)
6269  {
6270  return lhs.m_value.number_float == static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
6271  }
6272  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned and rhs_type == value_t::number_integer)
6273  {
6274  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) == rhs.m_value.number_integer;
6275  }
6276  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer and rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned)
6277  {
6278  return lhs.m_value.number_integer == static_cast<number_integer_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
6279  }
6280 
6281  return false;
6282  }

6373  friend bool operator<(const_reference lhs, const_reference rhs) noexcept
6374  {
6375  const auto lhs_type = lhs.type();
6376  const auto rhs_type = rhs.type();
6377 
6378  if (lhs_type == rhs_type)
6379  {
6380  switch (lhs_type)
6381  {
6382  case value_t::array:
6383  {
6384  return *lhs.m_value.array < *rhs.m_value.array;
6385  }
6386  case value_t::object:
6387  {
6388  return *lhs.m_value.object < *rhs.m_value.object;
6389  }
6390  case value_t::null:
6391  {
6392  return false;
6393  }
6394  case value_t::string:
6395  {
6396  return *lhs.m_value.string < *rhs.m_value.string;
6397  }
6398  case value_t::boolean:
6399  {
6400  return lhs.m_value.boolean < rhs.m_value.boolean;
6401  }
6402  case value_t::number_integer:
6403  {
6404  return lhs.m_value.number_integer < rhs.m_value.number_integer;
6405  }
6406  case value_t::number_unsigned:
6407  {
6408  return lhs.m_value.number_unsigned < rhs.m_value.number_unsigned;
6409  }
6410  case value_t::number_float:
6411  {
6412  return lhs.m_value.number_float < rhs.m_value.number_float;
6413  }
6414  default:
6415  {
6416  return false;
6417  }
6418  }
6419  }
6420  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer and rhs_type == value_t::number_float)
6421  {
6422  return static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_integer) < rhs.m_value.number_float;
6423  }
6424  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float and rhs_type == value_t::number_integer)
6425  {
6426  return lhs.m_value.number_float < static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_integer);
6427  }
6428  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned and rhs_type == value_t::number_float)
6429  {
6430  return static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) < rhs.m_value.number_float;
6431  }
6432  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float and rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned)
6433  {
6434  return lhs.m_value.number_float < static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
6435  }
6436  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer and rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned)
6437  {
6438  return lhs.m_value.number_integer < static_cast<number_integer_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
6439  }
6440  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned and rhs_type == value_t::number_integer)
6441  {
6442  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) < rhs.m_value.number_integer;
6443  }
6444 
6445  // We only reach this line if we cannot compare values. In that case,
6446  // we compare types. Note we have to call the operator explicitly,
6447  // because MSVC has problems otherwise.
6448  return operator<(lhs_type, rhs_type);
6449  }

6710 
6712  // serialization //
6714 
6717 
6718  private:
6722  class serializer
6723  {
6724  private:
6725  serializer(const serializer&) = delete;
6726  serializer& operator=(const serializer&) = delete;
6727 
6728  public:
6733  serializer(output_adapter_t<char> s, const char ichar)
6734  : o(s), loc(std::localeconv()),
6735  thousands_sep(!loc->thousands_sep ? '\0' : loc->thousands_sep[0]),
6736  decimal_point(!loc->decimal_point ? '\0' : loc->decimal_point[0]),
6737  indent_char(ichar), indent_string(512, indent_char)
6738  {}
6739 
6757  void dump(const basic_json& val,
6758  const bool pretty_print,
6759  const unsigned int indent_step,
6760  const unsigned int current_indent = 0)
6761  {
6762  switch (val.m_type)
6763  {
6764  case value_t::object:
6765  {
6766  if (val.m_value.object->empty())
6767  {
6768  o->write_characters("{}", 2);
6769  return;
6770  }
6771 
6772  if (pretty_print)
6773  {
6774  o->write_characters("{\n", 2);
6775 
6776  // variable to hold indentation for recursive calls
6777  const auto new_indent = current_indent + indent_step;
6778  if (indent_string.size() < new_indent)
6779  {
6780  indent_string.resize(new_indent, ' ');
6781  }
6782 
6783  // first n-1 elements
6784  auto i = val.m_value.object->cbegin();
6785  for (size_t cnt = 0; cnt < val.m_value.object->size() - 1; ++cnt, ++i)
6786  {
6787  o->write_characters(indent_string.c_str(), new_indent);
6788  o->write_character('\"');
6789  dump_escaped(i->first);
6790  o->write_characters("\": ", 3);
6791  dump(i->second, true, indent_step, new_indent);
6792  o->write_characters(",\n", 2);
6793  }
6794 
6795  // last element
6796  assert(i != val.m_value.object->cend());
6797  o->write_characters(indent_string.c_str(), new_indent);
6798  o->write_character('\"');
6799  dump_escaped(i->first);
6800  o->write_characters("\": ", 3);
6801  dump(i->second, true, indent_step, new_indent);
6802 
6803  o->write_character('\n');
6804  o->write_characters(indent_string.c_str(), current_indent);
6805  o->write_character('}');
6806  }
6807  else
6808  {
6809  o->write_character('{');
6810 
6811  // first n-1 elements
6812  auto i = val.m_value.object->cbegin();
6813  for (size_t cnt = 0; cnt < val.m_value.object->size() - 1; ++cnt, ++i)
6814  {
6815  o->write_character('\"');
6816  dump_escaped(i->first);
6817  o->write_characters("\":", 2);
6818  dump(i->second, false, indent_step, current_indent);
6819  o->write_character(',');
6820  }
6821 
6822  // last element
6823  assert(i != val.m_value.object->cend());
6824  o->write_character('\"');
6825  dump_escaped(i->first);
6826  o->write_characters("\":", 2);
6827  dump(i->second, false, indent_step, current_indent);
6828 
6829  o->write_character('}');
6830  }
6831 
6832  return;
6833  }
6834 
6835  case value_t::array:
6836  {
6837  if (val.m_value.array->empty())
6838  {
6839  o->write_characters("[]", 2);
6840  return;
6841  }
6842 
6843  if (pretty_print)
6844  {
6845  o->write_characters("[\n", 2);
6846 
6847  // variable to hold indentation for recursive calls
6848  const auto new_indent = current_indent + indent_step;
6849  if (indent_string.size() < new_indent)
6850  {
6851  indent_string.resize(new_indent, ' ');
6852  }
6853 
6854  // first n-1 elements
6855  for (auto i = val.m_value.array->cbegin(); i != val.m_value.array->cend() - 1; ++i)
6856  {
6857  o->write_characters(indent_string.c_str(), new_indent);
6858  dump(*i, true, indent_step, new_indent);
6859  o->write_characters(",\n", 2);
6860  }
6861 
6862  // last element
6863  assert(not val.m_value.array->empty());
6864  o->write_characters(indent_string.c_str(), new_indent);
6865  dump(val.m_value.array->back(), true, indent_step, new_indent);
6866 
6867  o->write_character('\n');
6868  o->write_characters(indent_string.c_str(), current_indent);
6869  o->write_character(']');
6870  }
6871  else
6872  {
6873  o->write_character('[');
6874 
6875  // first n-1 elements
6876  for (auto i = val.m_value.array->cbegin(); i != val.m_value.array->cend() - 1; ++i)
6877  {
6878  dump(*i, false, indent_step, current_indent);
6879  o->write_character(',');
6880  }
6881 
6882  // last element
6883  assert(not val.m_value.array->empty());
6884  dump(val.m_value.array->back(), false, indent_step, current_indent);
6885 
6886  o->write_character(']');
6887  }
6888 
6889  return;
6890  }
6891 
6892  case value_t::string:
6893  {
6894  o->write_character('\"');
6895  dump_escaped(*val.m_value.string);
6896  o->write_character('\"');
6897  return;
6898  }
6899 
6900  case value_t::boolean:
6901  {
6902  if (val.m_value.boolean)
6903  {
6904  o->write_characters("true", 4);
6905  }
6906  else
6907  {
6908  o->write_characters("false", 5);
6909  }
6910  return;
6911  }
6912 
6913  case value_t::number_integer:
6914  {
6915  dump_integer(val.m_value.number_integer);
6916  return;
6917  }
6918 
6919  case value_t::number_unsigned:
6920  {
6921  dump_integer(val.m_value.number_unsigned);
6922  return;
6923  }
6924 
6925  case value_t::number_float:
6926  {
6927  dump_float(val.m_value.number_float);
6928  return;
6929  }
6930 
6931  case value_t::discarded:
6932  {
6933  o->write_characters("<discarded>", 11);
6934  return;
6935  }
6936 
6937  case value_t::null:
6938  {
6939  o->write_characters("null", 4);
6940  return;
6941  }
6942  }
6943  }
6944 
6945  private:
6954  static std::size_t extra_space(const string_t& s) noexcept
6955  {
6956  return std::accumulate(s.begin(), s.end(), size_t{},
6957  [](size_t res, typename string_t::value_type c)
6958  {
6959  switch (c)
6960  {
6961  case '"':
6962  case '\\':
6963  case '\b':
6964  case '\f':
6965  case '\n':
6966  case '\r':
6967  case '\t':
6968  {
6969  // from c (1 byte) to \x (2 bytes)
6970  return res + 1;
6971  }
6972 
6973  case 0x00:
6974  case 0x01:
6975  case 0x02:
6976  case 0x03:
6977  case 0x04:
6978  case 0x05:
6979  case 0x06:
6980  case 0x07:
6981  case 0x0b:
6982  case 0x0e:
6983  case 0x0f:
6984  case 0x10:
6985  case 0x11:
6986  case 0x12:
6987  case 0x13:
6988  case 0x14:
6989  case 0x15:
6990  case 0x16:
6991  case 0x17:
6992  case 0x18:
6993  case 0x19:
6994  case 0x1a:
6995  case 0x1b:
6996  case 0x1c:
6997  case 0x1d:
6998  case 0x1e:
6999  case 0x1f:
7000  {
7001  // from c (1 byte) to \uxxxx (6 bytes)
7002  return res + 5;
7003  }
7004 
7005  default:
7006  {
7007  return res;
7008  }
7009  }
7010  });
7011  }
7012 
7025  void dump_escaped(const string_t& s) const
7026  {
7027  const auto space = extra_space(s);
7028  if (space == 0)
7029  {
7030  o->write_characters(s.c_str(), s.size());
7031  return;
7032  }
7033 
7034  // create a result string of necessary size
7035  string_t result(s.size() + space, '\\');
7036  std::size_t pos = 0;
7037 
7038  for (const auto& c : s)
7039  {
7040  switch (c)
7041  {
7042  // quotation mark (0x22)
7043  case '"':
7044  {
7045  result[pos + 1] = '"';
7046  pos += 2;
7047  break;
7048  }
7049 
7050  // reverse solidus (0x5c)
7051  case '\\':
7052  {
7053  // nothing to change
7054  pos += 2;
7055  break;
7056  }
7057 
7058  // backspace (0x08)
7059  case '\b':
7060  {
7061  result[pos + 1] = 'b';
7062  pos += 2;
7063  break;
7064  }
7065 
7066  // formfeed (0x0c)
7067  case '\f':
7068  {
7069  result[pos + 1] = 'f';
7070  pos += 2;
7071  break;
7072  }
7073 
7074  // newline (0x0a)
7075  case '\n':
7076  {
7077  result[pos + 1] = 'n';
7078  pos += 2;
7079  break;
7080  }
7081 
7082  // carriage return (0x0d)
7083  case '\r':
7084  {
7085  result[pos + 1] = 'r';
7086  pos += 2;
7087  break;
7088  }
7089 
7090  // horizontal tab (0x09)
7091  case '\t':
7092  {
7093  result[pos + 1] = 't';
7094  pos += 2;
7095  break;
7096  }
7097 
7098  case 0x00:
7099  case 0x01:
7100  case 0x02:
7101  case 0x03:
7102  case 0x04:
7103  case 0x05:
7104  case 0x06:
7105  case 0x07:
7106  case 0x0b:
7107  case 0x0e:
7108  case 0x0f:
7109  case 0x10:
7110  case 0x11:
7111  case 0x12:
7112  case 0x13:
7113  case 0x14:
7114  case 0x15:
7115  case 0x16:
7116  case 0x17:
7117  case 0x18:
7118  case 0x19:
7119  case 0x1a:
7120  case 0x1b:
7121  case 0x1c:
7122  case 0x1d:
7123  case 0x1e:
7124  case 0x1f:
7125  {
7126  // convert a number 0..15 to its hex representation
7127  // (0..f)
7128  static const char hexify[16] =
7129  {
7130  '0', '1', '2', '3', '4', '5', '6', '7',
7131  '8', '9', 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f'
7132  };
7133 
7134  // print character c as \uxxxx
7135  for (const char m :
7136  { 'u', '0', '0', hexify[c >> 4], hexify[c & 0x0f]
7137  })
7138  {
7139  result[++pos] = m;
7140  }
7141 
7142  ++pos;
7143  break;
7144  }
7145 
7146  default:
7147  {
7148  // all other characters are added as-is
7149  result[pos++] = c;
7150  break;
7151  }
7152  }
7153  }
7154 
7155  assert(pos == s.size() + space);
7156  o->write_characters(result.c_str(), result.size());
7157  }
7158 
7168  template<typename NumberType, detail::enable_if_t <
7169  std::is_same<NumberType, number_unsigned_t>::value or
7170  std::is_same<NumberType, number_integer_t>::value, int> = 0>
7171  void dump_integer(NumberType x)
7172  {
7173  // special case for "0"
7174  if (x == 0)
7175  {
7176  o->write_character('0');
7177  return;
7178  }
7179 
7180  const bool is_negative = x < 0;
7181  size_t i = 0;
7182 
7183  // spare 1 byte for '\0'
7184  while (x != 0 and i < number_buffer.size() - 1)
7185  {
7186  const auto digit = std::labs(static_cast<long>(x % 10));
7187  number_buffer[i++] = static_cast<char>('0' + digit);
7188  x /= 10;
7189  }
7190 
7191  // make sure the number has been processed completely
7192  assert(x == 0);
7193 
7194  if (is_negative)
7195  {
7196  // make sure there is capacity for the '-'
7197  assert(i < number_buffer.size() - 2);
7198  number_buffer[i++] = '-';
7199  }
7200 
7201  std::reverse(number_buffer.begin(), number_buffer.begin() + i);
7202  o->write_characters(number_buffer.data(), i);
7203  }
7204 
7213  void dump_float(number_float_t x)
7214  {
7215  // NaN / inf
7216  if (not std::isfinite(x) or std::isnan(x))
7217  {
7218  o->write_characters("null", 4);
7219  return;
7220  }
7221 
7222  // special case for 0.0 and -0.0
7223  if (x == 0)
7224  {
7225  if (std::signbit(x))
7226  {
7227  o->write_characters("-0.0", 4);
7228  }
7229  else
7230  {
7231  o->write_characters("0.0", 3);
7232  }
7233  return;
7234  }
7235 
7236  // get number of digits for a text -> float -> text round-trip
7237  static constexpr auto d = std::numeric_limits<number_float_t>::digits10;
7238 
7239  // the actual conversion
7240  std::ptrdiff_t len = snprintf(number_buffer.data(), number_buffer.size(),
7241  "%.*g", d, x);
7242 
7243  // negative value indicates an error
7244  assert(len > 0);
7245  // check if buffer was large enough
7246  assert(static_cast<size_t>(len) < number_buffer.size());
7247 
7248  // erase thousands separator
7249  if (thousands_sep != '\0')
7250  {
7251  const auto end = std::remove(number_buffer.begin(),
7252  number_buffer.begin() + len,
7253  thousands_sep);
7254  std::fill(end, number_buffer.end(), '\0');
7255  assert((end - number_buffer.begin()) <= len);
7256  len = (end - number_buffer.begin());
7257  }
7258 
7259  // convert decimal point to '.'
7260  if (decimal_point != '\0' and decimal_point != '.')
7261  {
7262  for (auto& c : number_buffer)
7263  {
7264  if (c == decimal_point)
7265  {
7266  c = '.';
7267  break;
7268  }
7269  }
7270  }
7271 
7272  o->write_characters(number_buffer.data(), static_cast<size_t>(len));
7273 
7274  // determine if need to append ".0"
7275  const bool value_is_int_like = std::none_of(number_buffer.begin(),
7276  number_buffer.begin() + len + 1,
7277  [](char c)
7278  {
7279  return c == '.' or c == 'e';
7280  });
7281 
7282  if (value_is_int_like)
7283  {
7284  o->write_characters(".0", 2);
7285  }
7286  }
7287 
7288  private:
7290  output_adapter_t<char> o = nullptr;
7291 
7293  std::array<char, 64> number_buffer{{}};
7294 
7296  const std::lconv* loc = nullptr;
7298  const char thousands_sep = '\0';
7300  const char decimal_point = '\0';
7301 
7303  const char indent_char;
7304 
7306  string_t indent_string;
7307  };
7308 
7309  public:
7338  friend std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& o, const basic_json& j)
7339  {
7340  // read width member and use it as indentation parameter if nonzero
7341  const bool pretty_print = (o.width() > 0);
7342  const auto indentation = (pretty_print ? o.width() : 0);
7343 
7344  // reset width to 0 for subsequent calls to this stream
7345  o.width(0);
7346 
7347  // do the actual serialization
7348  serializer s(output_adapter<char>::create(o), o.fill());
7349  s.dump(j, pretty_print, static_cast<unsigned int>(indentation));
7350  return o;
7351  }

7758  {

7783  {

7788  {

7878  template<typename IteratorType>
7879  class iteration_proxy
7880  {
7881  private:
7883  class iteration_proxy_internal
7884  {
7885  private:
7887  IteratorType anchor;
7889  size_t array_index = 0;
7890 
7891  public:
7892  explicit iteration_proxy_internal(IteratorType it) noexcept
7893  : anchor(it)
7894  {}
7895 
7897  iteration_proxy_internal& operator*()
7898  {
7899  return *this;
7900  }
7901 
7903  iteration_proxy_internal& operator++()
7904  {
7905  ++anchor;
7906  ++array_index;
7907 
7908  return *this;
7909  }
7910 
7912  bool operator!= (const iteration_proxy_internal& o) const
7913  {
7914  return anchor != o.anchor;
7915  }
7916 
7918  typename basic_json::string_t key() const
7919  {
7920  assert(anchor.m_object != nullptr);
7921 
7922  switch (anchor.m_object->type())
7923  {
7924  // use integer array index as key
7925  case value_t::array:
7926  {
7927  return std::to_string(array_index);
7928  }
7929 
7930  // use key from the object
7931  case value_t::object:
7932  {
7933  return anchor.key();
7934  }
7935 
7936  // use an empty key for all primitive types
7937  default:
7938  {
7939  return "";
7940  }
7941  }
7942  }
7943 
7945  typename IteratorType::reference value() const
7946  {
7947  return anchor.value();
7948  }
7949  };
7950 
7952  typename IteratorType::reference container;
7953 
7954  public:
7956  explicit iteration_proxy(typename IteratorType::reference cont)
7957  : container(cont)
7958  {}
7959 
7961  iteration_proxy_internal begin() noexcept
7962  {
7963  return iteration_proxy_internal(container.begin());
7964  }
7965

7968  {

7993  template<typename U>
7994  class iter_impl : public std::iterator<std::random_access_iterator_tag, U>
7995  {
7997  friend class basic_json;
7998 
7999  // make sure U is basic_json or const basic_json
8000  static_assert(std::is_same<U, basic_json>::value
8001  or std::is_same<U, const basic_json>::value,
8002  "iter_impl only accepts (const) basic_json");
8003 
8004  public:
8006  using value_type = typename basic_json::value_type;
8008  using difference_type = typename basic_json::difference_type;
8010  using pointer = typename std::conditional<std::is_const<U>::value,
8011  typename basic_json::const_pointer,
8012  typename basic_json::pointer>::type;
8014  using reference = typename std::conditional<std::is_const<U>::value,
8015  typename basic_json::const_reference,
8016  typename basic_json::reference>::type;
8018  using iterator_category = std::bidirectional_iterator_tag;
8019 
8021  iter_impl() = default;
8022 
8029  explicit iter_impl(pointer object) noexcept
8030  : m_object(object)
8031  {
8032  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8033 
8034  switch (m_object->m_type)
8035  {
8036  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8037  {
8038  m_it.object_iterator = typename object_t::iterator();
8039  break;
8040  }
8041 
8042  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8043  {
8044  m_it.array_iterator = typename array_t::iterator();
8045  break;
8046  }
8047 
8048  default:
8049  {
8050  m_it.primitive_iterator = primitive_iterator_t();
8051  break;
8052  }
8053  }
8054  }
8055 
8056  /*
8057  Use operator `const_iterator` instead of `const_iterator(const iterator&
8058  other) noexcept` to avoid two class definitions for @ref iterator and
8059  @ref const_iterator.
8060 
8061  This function is only called if this class is an @ref iterator. If this
8062  class is a @ref const_iterator this function is not called.
8063  */
8064  operator const_iterator() const
8065  {
8066  const_iterator ret;
8067 
8068  if (m_object)
8069  {
8070  ret.m_object = m_object;
8071  ret.m_it = m_it;
8072  }
8073 
8074  return ret;
8075  }
8076 
8082  iter_impl(const iter_impl& other) noexcept
8083  : m_object(other.m_object), m_it(other.m_it)
8084  {}
8085 
8091  iter_impl& operator=(iter_impl other) noexcept(
8092  std::is_nothrow_move_constructible<pointer>::value and
8093  std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<pointer>::value and
8094  std::is_nothrow_move_constructible<internal_iterator>::value and
8095  std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<internal_iterator>::value
8096  )
8097  {
8098  std::swap(m_object, other.m_object);
8099  std::swap(m_it, other.m_it);
8100  return *this;
8101  }
8102 
8103  private:
8108  void set_begin() noexcept
8109  {
8110  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8111 
8112  switch (m_object->m_type)
8113  {
8114  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8115  {
8116  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->begin();
8117  break;
8118  }
8119 
8120  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8121  {
8122  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->begin();
8123  break;
8124  }
8125 
8126  case basic_json::value_t::null:
8127  {
8128  // set to end so begin()==end() is true: null is empty
8129  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
8130  break;
8131  }
8132 
8133  default:
8134  {
8135  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_begin();
8136  break;
8137  }
8138  }
8139  }
8140 
8145  void set_end() noexcept
8146  {
8147  assert(m_object != nullptr);
8148 
8149  switch (m_object->m_type)
8150  {
8151  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8152  {
8153  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->end();
8154  break;
8155  }
8156 
8157  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8158  {
8159  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->end();
8160  break;
8161  }
8162 
8163  default:
8164  {
8165  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
8166  break;
8167  }
8168  }
8169  }

8171  public:

8177  {

8179

8181  {
8182  case basic_json::value_t::object:
8183  {
8184  assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
8185  return m_it.object_iterator->second;
8186  }
8187 
8188  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8189  {
8190  assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
8191  return *m_it.array_iterator;
8192  }
8193 
8194  case basic_json::value_t::null:
8195  {
8196  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
8197  }
8198 
8199  default:
8200  {
8201  if (m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin())
8202  {
8203  return *m_object;
8204  }
8205 
8206  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
8207  }
8208  }
8209  }

8225  }
8226

8230  return &*m_it.array_iterator;
8231  }

8236  {

8238  }
8239 
8240  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
8241  }
8242  }
8243  }

8340  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));

8350  }
8351 
8352  case basic_json::value_t::array:
8353  {
8354  return (m_it.array_iterator == other.m_it.array_iterator);
8355  }
8356 
8357  default:
8358  {

8360  }
8361  }
8362  }

8378  {
8379  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
8380  if (m_object != other.m_object)
8381  {
8382  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
8383  }

8710  class input_adapter
8711  {

8715  virtual ~input_adapter() {}
8716 
8717  // native support
8718 
8720  static std::shared_ptr<input_adapter> create(std::istream& i, const size_t buffer_size = 16384)
8721  {
8722  return std::shared_ptr<input_adapter>(new cached_input_stream_adapter(i, buffer_size));
8723  }
8724

8727  {

8729  }
8730 
8732  static std::shared_ptr<input_adapter> create(const char* b, size_t l)
8733  {
8734  return std::shared_ptr<input_adapter>(new input_buffer_adapter(b, l));
8735  }
8736 
8737  // derived support
8738 
8740  template<typename CharT, typename std::enable_if<
8741  std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
8742  std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
8743  sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1, int>::type = 0>
8744  static std::shared_ptr<input_adapter> create(CharT b)
8745  {
8746  return create(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b),
8747  std::strlen(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b)));
8748  }
8749 
8751  template<class IteratorType, typename std::enable_if<
8752  std::is_same<typename std::iterator_traits<IteratorType>::iterator_category, std::random_access_iterator_tag>::value
8753  , int>::type
8754  = 0>
8755  static std::shared_ptr<input_adapter> create(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
8756  {
8757  // assertion to check that the iterator range is indeed contiguous,
8758  // see http://stackoverflow.com/a/35008842/266378 for more discussion
8759  assert(std::accumulate(first, last, std::pair<bool, int>(true, 0),
8760  [&first](std::pair<bool, int> res, decltype(*first) val)
8761  {
8762  res.first &= (val == *(std::next(std::addressof(*first), res.second++)));
8763  return res;
8764  }).first);
8765 
8766  // assertion to check that each element is 1 byte long
8767  static_assert(sizeof(typename std::iterator_traits<IteratorType>::value_type) == 1,
8768  "each element in the iterator range must have the size of 1 byte");
8769 
8770  return create(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(&(*first)),
8771  static_cast<size_t>(std::distance(first, last)));
8772  }
8773 
8775  template<class T, std::size_t N>
8776  static std::shared_ptr<input_adapter> create(T (&array)[N])
8777  {
8778  // delegate the call to the iterator-range overload
8779  return create(std::begin(array), std::end(array));
8780  }
8781 
8783  template<class ContiguousContainer, typename std::enable_if<
8784  not std::is_pointer<ContiguousContainer>::value and
8785  std::is_base_of<
8786  std::random_access_iterator_tag,
8787  typename std::iterator_traits<decltype(std::begin(std::declval<ContiguousContainer const>()))>::iterator_category>::value
8788  , int>::type = 0>
8789  static std::shared_ptr<input_adapter> create(const ContiguousContainer& c)
8790  {
8791  // delegate the call to the iterator-range overload
8792  return create(std::begin(c), std::end(c));
8793  }
8794  };
8795 
8797  using input_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<input_adapter>;
8798 
8800  class cached_input_stream_adapter : public input_adapter
8801  {
8802  public:
8803  cached_input_stream_adapter(std::istream& i, const size_t buffer_size)
8804  : is(i), start_position(is.tellg()), buffer(buffer_size, '\0')
8805  {
8806  // immediately abort if stream is erroneous
8807  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(i.fail()))
8808  {
8809  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(111, 0, "bad input stream"));
8810  }
8811 
8812  // initial fill
8813  is.read(buffer.data(), static_cast<std::streamsize>(buffer.size()));
8814  // store number of bytes in the buffer
8815  fill_size = static_cast<size_t>(is.gcount());
8816 
8817  // skip byte-order mark
8818  if (fill_size >= 3 and buffer[0] == '\xEF' and buffer[1] == '\xBB' and buffer[2] == '\xBF')
8819  {
8820  buffer_pos += 3;
8821  processed_chars += 3;
8822  }
8823  }
8824 
8825  ~cached_input_stream_adapter() override
8826  {
8827  // clear stream flags
8828  is.clear();
8829  // set stream after last processed char
8830  is.seekg(start_position + static_cast<std::streamoff>(processed_chars - 1));
8831  }
8832 
8833  int get_character() override
8834  {
8835  // check if refilling is necessary and possible
8836  if (buffer_pos == fill_size and not eof)
8837  {
8838  // refill
8839  is.read(buffer.data(), static_cast<std::streamsize>(buffer.size()));
8840  // store number of bytes in the buffer
8841  fill_size = static_cast<size_t>(is.gcount());
8842 
8843  // remember that filling did not yield new input
8844  if (fill_size == 0)
8845  {
8846  eof = true;
8847  }
8848 
8849  // the buffer is ready
8850  buffer_pos = 0;
8851  }
8852 
8853  ++processed_chars;
8854  return eof
8855  ? std::char_traits<char>::eof()
8856  : buffer[buffer_pos++] & 0xFF;
8857  }
8858 
8859  std::string read(size_t offset, size_t length) override
8860  {
8861  // create buffer
8862  std::string result(length, '\0');
8863 
8864  // save stream position
8865  auto current_pos = is.tellg();
8866  // save stream flags
8867  auto flags = is.rdstate();
8868 
8869  // clear stream flags
8870  is.clear();
8871  // set stream position
8872  is.seekg(static_cast<std::streamoff>(offset));
8873  // read bytes
8874  is.read(&result[0], static_cast<std::streamsize>(length));
8875 
8876  // reset stream position
8877  is.seekg(current_pos);
8878  // reset stream flags
8879  is.setstate(flags);
8880 
8881  return result;
8882  }
8883 
8884  private:
8886  std::istream& is;
8887 
8889  size_t processed_chars = 0;
8891  size_t buffer_pos = 0;
8892 
8894  bool eof = false;
8896  size_t fill_size = 0;
8897 
8899  const std::streampos start_position;
8900 
8902  std::vector<char> buffer;
8903  };
8904 
8906  class input_buffer_adapter : public input_adapter
8907  {
8908  public:
8909  input_buffer_adapter(const char* b, size_t l)
8910  : input_adapter(), cursor(b), limit(b + l), start(b)
8911  {}
8912 
8913  // delete because of pointer members
8914  input_buffer_adapter(const input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
8915  input_buffer_adapter& operator=(input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
8916 
8917  int get_character() override
8918  {
8919  if (JSON_LIKELY(cursor < limit))
8920  {
8921  return *(cursor++) & 0xFF;
8922  }
8923  else
8924  {
8925  return std::char_traits<char>::eof();
8926  }
8927  }
8928 
8929  std::string read(size_t offset, size_t length) override
8930  {
8931  // avoid reading too many characters
8932  const size_t max_length = static_cast<size_t>(limit - start);
8933  return std::string(start + offset, std::min(length, max_length - offset));
8934  }
8935 
8936  private:
8938  const char* cursor;
8940  const char* limit;
8942  const char* start;
8943  };

8946  // binary serialization/deserialization //
8948 
8951 
8952  private:
8956  class binary_reader
8957  {
8958  public:
8964  explicit binary_reader(input_adapter_t adapter)
8965  : ia(adapter), is_little_endian(little_endianess())
8966  {
8967  assert(ia);
8968  }
8969 
8982  basic_json parse_cbor(const bool get_char = true)
8983  {
8984  switch (get_char ? get() : current)
8985  {
8986  // EOF
8987  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
8988  {
8989  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "unexpected end of input"));
8990  }
8991 
8992  // Integer 0x00..0x17 (0..23)
8993  case 0x00:
8994  case 0x01:
8995  case 0x02:
8996  case 0x03:
8997  case 0x04:
8998  case 0x05:
8999  case 0x06:
9000  case 0x07:
9001  case 0x08:
9002  case 0x09:
9003  case 0x0a:
9004  case 0x0b:
9005  case 0x0c:
9006  case 0x0d:
9007  case 0x0e:
9008  case 0x0f:
9009  case 0x10:
9010  case 0x11:
9011  case 0x12:
9012  case 0x13:
9013  case 0x14:
9014  case 0x15:
9015  case 0x16:
9016  case 0x17:
9017  {
9018  return static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(current);
9019  }
9020 
9021  case 0x18: // Unsigned integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
9022  {
9023  return get_number<uint8_t>();
9024  }
9025 
9026  case 0x19: // Unsigned integer (two-byte uint16_t follows)
9027  {
9028  return get_number<uint16_t>();
9029  }
9030 
9031  case 0x1a: // Unsigned integer (four-byte uint32_t follows)
9032  {
9033  return get_number<uint32_t>();
9034  }
9035

9319  case 0xf5: // true

9321  return true;
9322  }

9324  case 0xf6: // null
9325  {
9326  return value_t::null;
9327  }
9328 
9329  case 0xf9: // Half-Precision Float (two-byte IEEE 754)
9330  {
9331  const int byte1 = get();
9332  check_eof();
9333  const int byte2 = get();
9334  check_eof();
9335 
9336  // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
9337  // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added
9338  // to IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often
9339  // still only have limited support for them. It is very
9340  // easy to include at least decoding support for them even
9341  // without such support. An example of a small decoder for
9342  // half-precision floating-point numbers in the C language
9343  // is shown in Fig. 3.
9344  const int half = (byte1 << 8) + byte2;
9345  const int exp = (half >> 10) & 0x1f;
9346  const int mant = half & 0x3ff;
9347  double val;
9348  if (exp == 0)
9349  {
9350  val = std::ldexp(mant, -24);
9351  }
9352  else if (exp != 31)
9353  {
9354  val = std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
9355  }
9356  else
9357  {
9358  val = mant == 0
9359  ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()
9360  : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
9361  }
9362  return (half & 0x8000) != 0 ? -val : val;
9363  }
9364 
9365  case 0xfa: // Single-Precision Float (four-byte IEEE 754)
9366  {
9367  return get_number<float>();
9368  }
9369 
9370  case 0xfb: // Double-Precision Float (eight-byte IEEE 754)
9371  {
9372  return get_number<double>();
9373  }
9374 
9375  default: // anything else (0xFF is handled inside the other types)
9376  {
9377  std::stringstream ss;
9378  ss << std::setw(2) << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
9379  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(112, chars_read, "error reading CBOR; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
9380  }
9381  }
9382  }

9792  }
