9801  static bool little_endianess() noexcept
9802  {
9803  int num = 1;
9804  return (*reinterpret_cast<char*>(&num) == 1);
9805  }
9806 
9807  private:
9817  int get()
9818  {
9819  ++chars_read;
9820  return (current = ia->get_character());
9821  }
9822 
9823  /*
9824  @brief read a number from the input
9825 
9826  @tparam T the type of the number
9827 
9828  @return number of type @a T
9829 
9830  @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because
9831  bytes in CBOR and MessagePack are stored in network order (big
9832  endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
9833 
9834  @throw parse_error.110 if input has less than `sizeof(T)` bytes
9835  */
9836  template<typename T>
9837  T get_number()
9838  {
9839  // step 1: read input into array with system's byte order
9840  std::array<uint8_t, sizeof(T)> vec;
9841  for (size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(T); ++i)
9842  {
9843  get();
9844  check_eof();
9845 
9846  // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
9847  if (is_little_endian)
9848  {
9849  vec[sizeof(T) - i - 1] = static_cast<uint8_t>(current);
9850  }
9851  else
9852  {
9853  vec[i] = static_cast<uint8_t>(current);
9854  }
9855  }
9856 
9857  // step 2: convert array into number of type T and return
9858  T result;
9859  std::memcpy(&result, vec.data(), sizeof(T));
9860  return result;
9861  }
9862 
9872  std::string get_string(const size_t len)
9873  {
9874  std::string result;
9875  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
9876  {
9877  get();
9878  check_eof();
9879  result.append(1, static_cast<char>(current));
9880  }
9881  return result;
9882  }
9883 
9896  std::string get_cbor_string()
9897  {
9898  check_eof();
9899 
9900  switch (current)
9901  {
9902  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
9903  case 0x60:
9904  case 0x61:
9905  case 0x62:
9906  case 0x63:
9907  case 0x64:
9908  case 0x65:
9909  case 0x66:
9910  case 0x67:
9911  case 0x68:
9912  case 0x69:
9913  case 0x6a:
9914  case 0x6b:
9915  case 0x6c:
9916  case 0x6d:
9917  case 0x6e:
9918  case 0x6f:
9919  case 0x70:
9920  case 0x71:
9921  case 0x72:
9922  case 0x73:
9923  case 0x74:
9924  case 0x75:
9925  case 0x76:
9926  case 0x77:
9927  {
9928  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(current & 0x1f);
9929  return get_string(len);
9930  }
9931 
9932  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
9933  {
9934  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_number<uint8_t>());
9935  return get_string(len);
9936  }
9937 
9938  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
9939  {
9940  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_number<uint16_t>());
9941  return get_string(len);
9942  }
9943 
9944  case 0x7a: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
9945  {
9946  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_number<uint32_t>());
9947  return get_string(len);
9948  }
9949 
9950  case 0x7b: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
9951  {
9952  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_number<uint64_t>());
9953  return get_string(len);
9954  }
9955 
9956  case 0x7f: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
9957  {
9958  std::string result;
9959  while (get() != 0xff)
9960  {
9961  check_eof();
9962  result.append(1, static_cast<char>(current));
9963  }
9964  return result;
9965  }
9966 
9967  default:
9968  {
9969  std::stringstream ss;
9970  ss << std::setw(2) << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
9971  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(113, chars_read, "expected a CBOR string; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
9972  }
9973  }
9974  }
9975 
9987  std::string get_msgpack_string()
9988  {
9989  check_eof();
9990 
9991  switch (current)
9992  {
9993  // fixstr
9994  case 0xa0:
9995  case 0xa1:
9996  case 0xa2:
9997  case 0xa3:
9998  case 0xa4:
9999  case 0xa5:
10000  case 0xa6:
10001  case 0xa7:
10002  case 0xa8:
10003  case 0xa9:
10004  case 0xaa:
10005  case 0xab:
10006  case 0xac:
10007  case 0xad:
10008  case 0xae:
10009  case 0xaf:
10010  case 0xb0:
10011  case 0xb1:
10012  case 0xb2:
10013  case 0xb3:
10014  case 0xb4:
10015  case 0xb5:
10016  case 0xb6:
10017  case 0xb7:
10018  case 0xb8:
10019  case 0xb9:
10020  case 0xba:
10021  case 0xbb:
10022  case 0xbc:
10023  case 0xbd:
10024  case 0xbe:
10025  case 0xbf:
10026  {
10027  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(current & 0x1f);
10028  return get_string(len);
10029  }
10030 
10031  case 0xd9: // str 8
10032  {
10033  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_number<uint8_t>());
10034  return get_string(len);
10035  }
10036 
10037  case 0xda: // str 16
10038  {
10039  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_number<uint16_t>());
10040  return get_string(len);
10041  }
10042 
10043  case 0xdb: // str 32
10044  {
10045  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(get_number<uint32_t>());
10046  return get_string(len);
10047  }
10048 
10049  default:
10050  {
10051  std::stringstream ss;
10052  ss << std::setw(2) << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
10053  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(113, chars_read, "expected a MessagePack string; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
10054  }
10055  }
10056  }
10057 
10062  void check_eof() const
10063  {
10064  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current == std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
10065  {
10066  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "unexpected end of input"));
10067  }
10068  }
10069 
10070  private:
10072  input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
10073 
10075  int current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
10076 
10078  size_t chars_read = 0;
10079 
10081  const bool is_little_endian = true;
10082  };
10083 
10087  class binary_writer
10088  {
10089  public:
10095  explicit binary_writer(output_adapter_t<uint8_t> adapter)
10096  : is_little_endian(binary_reader::little_endianess()), oa(adapter)
10097  {
10098  assert(oa);
10099  }
10100 
10104  void write_cbor(const basic_json& j)
10105  {
10106  switch (j.type())
10107  {
10108  case value_t::null:
10109  {
10110  oa->write_character(0xf6);
10111  break;
10112  }
10113 
10114  case value_t::boolean:
10115  {
10116  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean ? 0xf5 : 0xf4);
10117  break;
10118  }
10119 
10120  case value_t::number_integer:
10121  {
10122  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
10123  {
10124  // CBOR does not differentiate between positive signed
10125  // integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used the
10126  // code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
10127  if (j.m_value.number_integer <= 0x17)
10128  {
10129  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10130  }
10131  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
10132  {
10133  oa->write_character(0x18);
10134  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10135  }
10136  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
10137  {
10138  oa->write_character(0x19);
10139  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10140  }
10141  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
10142  {
10143  oa->write_character(0x1a);
10144  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10145  }
10146  else
10147  {
10148  oa->write_character(0x1b);
10149  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10150  }
10151  }
10152  else
10153  {
10154  // The conversions below encode the sign in the first
10155  // byte, and the value is converted to a positive number.
10156  const auto positive_number = -1 - j.m_value.number_integer;
10157  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -24)
10158  {
10159  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x20 + positive_number));
10160  }
10161  else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
10162  {
10163  oa->write_character(0x38);
10164  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(positive_number));
10165  }
10166  else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
10167  {
10168  oa->write_character(0x39);
10169  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(positive_number));
10170  }
10171  else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
10172  {
10173  oa->write_character(0x3a);
10174  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(positive_number));
10175  }
10176  else
10177  {
10178  oa->write_character(0x3b);
10179  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(positive_number));
10180  }
10181  }
10182  break;
10183  }
10184 
10185  case value_t::number_unsigned:
10186  {
10187  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0x17)
10188  {
10189  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
10190  }
10191  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
10192  {
10193  oa->write_character(0x18);
10194  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
10195  }
10196  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
10197  {
10198  oa->write_character(0x19);
10199  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
10200  }
10201  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
10202  {
10203  oa->write_character(0x1a);
10204  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
10205  }
10206  else
10207  {
10208  oa->write_character(0x1b);
10209  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
10210  }
10211  break;
10212  }
10213 
10214  case value_t::number_float:
10215  {
10216  // Double-Precision Float
10217  oa->write_character(0xfb);
10218  write_number(j.m_value.number_float);
10219  break;
10220  }
10221 
10222  case value_t::string:
10223  {
10224  // step 1: write control byte and the string length
10225  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
10226  if (N <= 0x17)
10227  {
10228  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x60 + N));
10229  }
10230  else if (N <= 0xff)
10231  {
10232  oa->write_character(0x78);
10233  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(N));
10234  }
10235  else if (N <= 0xffff)
10236  {
10237  oa->write_character(0x79);
10238  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
10239  }
10240  else if (N <= 0xffffffff)
10241  {
10242  oa->write_character(0x7a);
10243  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
10244  }
10245  // LCOV_EXCL_START
10246  else if (N <= 0xffffffffffffffff)
10247  {
10248  oa->write_character(0x7b);
10249  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(N));
10250  }
10251  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10252 
10253  // step 2: write the string
10254  oa->write_characters(reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
10255  j.m_value.string->size());
10256  break;
10257  }
10258 
10259  case value_t::array:
10260  {
10261  // step 1: write control byte and the array size
10262  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
10263  if (N <= 0x17)
10264  {
10265  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x80 + N));
10266  }
10267  else if (N <= 0xff)
10268  {
10269  oa->write_character(0x98);
10270  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(N));
10271  }
10272  else if (N <= 0xffff)
10273  {
10274  oa->write_character(0x99);
10275  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
10276  }
10277  else if (N <= 0xffffffff)
10278  {
10279  oa->write_character(0x9a);
10280  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
10281  }
10282  // LCOV_EXCL_START
10283  else if (N <= 0xffffffffffffffff)
10284  {
10285  oa->write_character(0x9b);
10286  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(N));
10287  }
10288  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10289 
10290  // step 2: write each element
10291  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
10292  {
10293  write_cbor(el);
10294  }
10295  break;
10296  }
10297 
10298  case value_t::object:
10299  {
10300  // step 1: write control byte and the object size
10301  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
10302  if (N <= 0x17)
10303  {
10304  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0xa0 + N));
10305  }
10306  else if (N <= 0xff)
10307  {
10308  oa->write_character(0xb8);
10309  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(N));
10310  }
10311  else if (N <= 0xffff)
10312  {
10313  oa->write_character(0xb9);
10314  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
10315  }
10316  else if (N <= 0xffffffff)
10317  {
10318  oa->write_character(0xba);
10319  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
10320  }
10321  // LCOV_EXCL_START
10322  else if (N <= 0xffffffffffffffff)
10323  {
10324  oa->write_character(0xbb);
10325  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(N));
10326  }
10327  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10328 
10329  // step 2: write each element
10330  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
10331  {
10332  write_cbor(el.first);
10333  write_cbor(el.second);
10334  }
10335  break;
10336  }
10337 
10338  default:
10339  {
10340  break;
10341  }
10342  }
10343  }
10344 
10348  void write_msgpack(const basic_json& j)
10349  {
10350  switch (j.type())
10351  {
10352  case value_t::null:
10353  {
10354  // nil
10355  oa->write_character(0xc0);
10356  break;
10357  }
10358 
10359  case value_t::boolean:
10360  {
10361  // true and false
10362  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean ? 0xc3 : 0xc2);
10363  break;
10364  }
10365 
10366  case value_t::number_integer:
10367  {
10368  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
10369  {
10370  // MessagePack does not differentiate between positive
10371  // signed integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we
10372  // used the code from the value_t::number_unsigned case
10373  // here.
10374  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
10375  {
10376  // positive fixnum
10377  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10378  }
10379  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
10380  {
10381  // uint 8
10382  oa->write_character(0xcc);
10383  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10384  }
10385  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
10386  {
10387  // uint 16
10388  oa->write_character(0xcd);
10389  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10390  }
10391  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
10392  {
10393  // uint 32
10394  oa->write_character(0xce);
10395  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10396  }
10397  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max)())
10398  {
10399  // uint 64
10400  oa->write_character(0xcf);
10401  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10402  }
10403  }
10404  else
10405  {
10406  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -32)
10407  {
10408  // negative fixnum
10409  write_number(static_cast<int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10410  }
10411  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::min)() and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max)())
10412  {
10413  // int 8
10414  oa->write_character(0xd0);
10415  write_number(static_cast<int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10416  }
10417  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::min)() and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max)())
10418  {
10419  // int 16
10420  oa->write_character(0xd1);
10421  write_number(static_cast<int16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10422  }
10423  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min)() and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max)())
10424  {
10425  // int 32
10426  oa->write_character(0xd2);
10427  write_number(static_cast<int32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10428  }
10429  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min)() and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)())
10430  {
10431  // int 64
10432  oa->write_character(0xd3);
10433  write_number(static_cast<int64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10434  }
10435  }
10436  break;
10437  }
10438 
10439  case value_t::number_unsigned:
10440  {
10441  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
10442  {
10443  // positive fixnum
10444  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10445  }
10446  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
10447  {
10448  // uint 8
10449  oa->write_character(0xcc);
10450  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10451  }
10452  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
10453  {
10454  // uint 16
10455  oa->write_character(0xcd);
10456  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10457  }
10458  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
10459  {
10460  // uint 32
10461  oa->write_character(0xce);
10462  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10463  }
10464  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max)())
10465  {
10466  // uint 64
10467  oa->write_character(0xcf);
10468  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10469  }
10470  break;
10471  }
10472 
10473  case value_t::number_float:
10474  {
10475  // float 64
10476  oa->write_character(0xcb);
10477  write_number(j.m_value.number_float);
10478  break;
10479  }
10480 
10481  case value_t::string:
10482  {
10483  // step 1: write control byte and the string length
10484  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
10485  if (N <= 31)
10486  {
10487  // fixstr
10488  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0xa0 | N));
10489  }
10490  else if (N <= 255)
10491  {
10492  // str 8
10493  oa->write_character(0xd9);
10494  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(N));
10495  }
10496  else if (N <= 65535)
10497  {
10498  // str 16
10499  oa->write_character(0xda);
10500  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
10501  }
10502  else if (N <= 4294967295)
10503  {
10504  // str 32
10505  oa->write_character(0xdb);
10506  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
10507  }
10508 
10509  // step 2: write the string
10510  oa->write_characters(reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
10511  j.m_value.string->size());
10512  break;
10513  }
10514 
10515  case value_t::array:
10516  {
10517  // step 1: write control byte and the array size
10518  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
10519  if (N <= 15)
10520  {
10521  // fixarray
10522  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x90 | N));
10523  }
10524  else if (N <= 0xffff)
10525  {
10526  // array 16
10527  oa->write_character(0xdc);
10528  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
10529  }
10530  else if (N <= 0xffffffff)
10531  {
10532  // array 32
10533  oa->write_character(0xdd);
10534  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
10535  }
10536 
10537  // step 2: write each element
10538  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
10539  {
10540  write_msgpack(el);
10541  }
10542  break;
10543  }
10544 
10545  case value_t::object:
10546  {
10547  // step 1: write control byte and the object size
10548  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
10549  if (N <= 15)
10550  {
10551  // fixmap
10552  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x80 | (N & 0xf)));
10553  }
10554  else if (N <= 65535)
10555  {
10556  // map 16
10557  oa->write_character(0xde);
10558  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
10559  }
10560  else if (N <= 4294967295)
10561  {
10562  // map 32
10563  oa->write_character(0xdf);
10564  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
10565  }
10566 
10567  // step 2: write each element
10568  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
10569  {
10570  write_msgpack(el.first);
10571  write_msgpack(el.second);
10572  }
10573  break;
10574  }
10575 
10576  default:
10577  {
10578  break;
10579  }
10580  }
10581  }
10582 
10583  private:
10584  /*
10585  @brief write a number to output input
10586 
10587  @param[in] n number of type @a T
10588  @tparam T the type of the number
10589 
10590  @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because
10591  bytes in CBOR and MessagePack are stored in network order (big
10592  endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
10593  */
10594  template<typename T>
10595  void write_number(T n)
10596  {
10597  // step 1: write number to array of length T
10598  std::array<uint8_t, sizeof(T)> vec;
10599  std::memcpy(vec.data(), &n, sizeof(T));
10600 
10601  // step 2: write array to output (with possible reordering)
10602  for (size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(T); ++i)
10603  {
10604  // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
10605  if (is_little_endian)
10606  {
10607  oa->write_character(vec[sizeof(T) - i - 1]);
10608  }
10609  else
10610  {
10611  oa->write_character(vec[i]);
10612  }
10613  }
10614  }
10615 
10616  private:
10618  const bool is_little_endian = true;
10619 
10621  output_adapter_t<uint8_t> oa = nullptr;
10622  };
10623 
10624  public:
10707  static std::vector<uint8_t> to_cbor(const basic_json& j)
10708  {
10709  std::vector<uint8_t> result;
10710  binary_writer bw(output_adapter<uint8_t>::create(result));
10711  bw.write_cbor(j);
10712  return result;
10713  }
10714 
10789  static std::vector<uint8_t> to_msgpack(const basic_json& j)
10790  {
10791  std::vector<uint8_t> result;
10792  binary_writer bw(output_adapter<uint8_t>::create(result));
10793  bw.write_msgpack(j);
10794  return result;
10795  }
10796 
10884  static basic_json from_cbor(const std::vector<uint8_t>& v,
10885  const size_t start_index = 0)
10886  {
10887  binary_reader br(input_adapter::create(v.begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(start_index), v.end()));
10888  return br.parse_cbor();
10889  }
10890 
10891 
10959  static basic_json from_msgpack(const std::vector<uint8_t>& v,
10960  const size_t start_index = 0)
10961  {
10962  binary_reader br(input_adapter::create(v.begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(start_index), v.end()));
10963  return br.parse_msgpack();
10964  }

10972  private:
10978  class lexer
10979  {
10980  public:
10982  enum class token_type
10983  {
10984  uninitialized,
10985  literal_true,
10986  literal_false,
10987  literal_null,
10988  value_string,
10989  value_unsigned,
10990  value_integer,
10991  value_float,
10992  begin_array,
10993  begin_object,
10994  end_array,
10995  end_object,
10996  name_separator,
10997  value_separator,
10998  parse_error,
10999  end_of_input
11000  };
11001 
11003  static const char* token_type_name(const token_type t) noexcept
11004  {
11005  switch (t)
11006  {
11007  case token_type::uninitialized:
11008  return "<uninitialized>";
11009  case token_type::literal_true:
11010  return "true literal";
11011  case token_type::literal_false:
11012  return "false literal";
11013  case token_type::literal_null:
11014  return "null literal";
11015  case token_type::value_string:
11016  return "string literal";
11017  case lexer::token_type::value_unsigned:
11018  case lexer::token_type::value_integer:
11019  case lexer::token_type::value_float:
11020  return "number literal";
11021  case token_type::begin_array:
11022  return "'['";
11023  case token_type::begin_object:
11024  return "'{'";
11025  case token_type::end_array:
11026  return "']'";
11027  case token_type::end_object:
11028  return "'}'";
11029  case token_type::name_separator:
11030  return "':'";
11031  case token_type::value_separator:
11032  return "','";
11033  case token_type::parse_error:
11034  return "<parse error>";
11035  case token_type::end_of_input:
11036  return "end of input";
11037  default:
11038  {
11039  // catch non-enum values
11040  return "unknown token"; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
11041  }
11042  }
11043  }

11072  int get_codepoint()
11073  {

11075  assert(current == 'u');
11076  int codepoint = 0;
11077 
11078  // byte 1: \uXxxx
11079  switch (get())
11080  {
11081  case '0':
11082  break;
11083  case '1':
11084  codepoint += 0x1000;
11085  break;
11086  case '2':
11087  codepoint += 0x2000;
11088  break;
11089  case '3':
11090  codepoint += 0x3000;
11091  break;
11092  case '4':
11093  codepoint += 0x4000;
11094  break;
11095  case '5':
11096  codepoint += 0x5000;
11097  break;
11098  case '6':
11099  codepoint += 0x6000;
11100  break;
11101  case '7':
11102  codepoint += 0x7000;
11103  break;
11104  case '8':
11105  codepoint += 0x8000;
11106  break;
11107  case '9':
11108  codepoint += 0x9000;
11109  break;
11110  case 'A':
11111  case 'a':
11112  codepoint += 0xa000;
11113  break;
11114  case 'B':
11115  case 'b':
11116  codepoint += 0xb000;
11117  break;
11118  case 'C':
11119  case 'c':
11120  codepoint += 0xc000;
11121  break;
11122  case 'D':
11123  case 'd':
11124  codepoint += 0xd000;
11125  break;
11126  case 'E':
11127  case 'e':
11128  codepoint += 0xe000;
11129  break;
11130  case 'F':
11131  case 'f':
11132  codepoint += 0xf000;
11133  break;
11134  default:
11135  return -1;
11136  }

11139  switch (get())
11140  {
11141  case '0':
11142  break;
11143  case '1':
11144  codepoint += 0x0100;
11145  break;
11146  case '2':
11147  codepoint += 0x0200;
11148  break;
11149  case '3':
11150  codepoint += 0x0300;
11151  break;
11152  case '4':

11154  break;

11156  codepoint += 0x0500;
11157  break;

11160  break;

11163  break;

11166  break;

11169  break;

11177  break;
11178  case 'C':
11179  case 'c':
11180  codepoint += 0x0c00;
11181  break;
11182  case 'D':
11183  case 'd':
11184  codepoint += 0x0d00;
11185  break;
11186  case 'E':
11187  case 'e':
11188  codepoint += 0x0e00;
11189  break;

11265  break;

11268  break;

11298  case 'C':
11299  case 'c':
11300  codepoint += 0x000c;
11301  break;
11302  case 'D':
11303  case 'd':
11304  codepoint += 0x000d;
11305  break;
11306  case 'E':
11307  case 'e':
11308  codepoint += 0x000e;
11309  break;
11310  case 'F':
11311  case 'f':
11312  codepoint += 0x000f;
11313  break;
11314  default:

11316  }
11317

11319  }
11320 
11325  static std::string codepoint_to_string(int codepoint)
11326  {
11327  std::stringstream ss;
11328  ss << "U+" << std::setw(4) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << codepoint;
11329  return ss.str();
11330  }
11331 
11346  token_type scan_string()
11347  {
11348  // reset yytext (ignore opening quote)
11349  reset();
11350 
11351  // we entered the function by reading an open quote
11352  assert(current == '\"');
11353 
11354  while (true)
11355  {
11356  // get next character
11357  get();
11358 
11359  switch (current)
11360  {
11361  // end of file while parsing string
11362  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
11363  {
11364  error_message = "invalid string: missing closing quote";
11365  return token_type::parse_error;
11366  }
11367 
11368  // closing quote
11369  case '\"':
11370  {
11371  // terminate yytext
11372  add('\0');
11373  --yylen;
11374  return token_type::value_string;
11375  }
11376 
11377  // escapes
11378  case '\\':
11379  {
11380  switch (get())
11381  {
11382  // quotation mark
11383  case '\"':
11384  add('\"');
11385  break;
11386  // reverse solidus
11387  case '\\':
11388  add('\\');
11389  break;
11390  // solidus
11391  case '/':
11392  add('/');
11393  break;
11394  // backspace
11395  case 'b':
11396  add('\b');
11397  break;
11398  // form feed
11399  case 'f':
11400  add('\f');
11401  break;
11402  // line feed
11403  case 'n':
11404  add('\n');
11405  break;
11406  // carriage return
11407  case 'r':
11408  add('\r');
11409  break;
11410  // tab
11411  case 't':
11412  add('\t');
11413  break;
11414 
11415  // unicode escapes
11416  case 'u':
11417  {
11418  int codepoint;
11419  int codepoint1 = get_codepoint();
11420 
11421  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint1 == -1))
11422  {
11423  error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
11424  return token_type::parse_error;
11425  }
11426 
11427  // check if code point is a high surrogate
11428  if (0xD800 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF)
11429  {
11430  // expect next \uxxxx entry
11431  if (JSON_LIKELY(get() == '\\' and get() == 'u'))
11432  {
11433  const int codepoint2 = get_codepoint();
11434 
11435  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint2 == -1))
11436  {
11437  error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
11438  return token_type::parse_error;
11439  }
11440 
11441  // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
11442  if (JSON_LIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint2 and codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF))
11443  {
11444  codepoint =
11445  // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
11446  (codepoint1 << 10)
11447  // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
11448  + codepoint2
11449  // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
11450  // in the result so we have to subtract with:
11451  // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
11452  - 0x35FDC00;
11453  }
11454  else
11455  {
11456  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate " + codepoint_to_string(codepoint1) + " must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF instead of " + codepoint_to_string(codepoint2);
11457  return token_type::parse_error;
11458  }
11459  }
11460  else
11461  {
11462  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate " + codepoint_to_string(codepoint1) + " must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
11463  return token_type::parse_error;
11464  }
11465  }
11466  else
11467  {
11468  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDFFF))
11469  {
11470  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate " + codepoint_to_string(codepoint1) + " must follow U+D800..U+DBFF";
11471  return token_type::parse_error;
11472  }
11473 
11474  // only work with first code point
11475  codepoint = codepoint1;
11476  }
11477 
11478  // result of the above calculation yields a proper codepoint
11479  assert(0x00 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0x10FFFF);
11480 
11481  // translate code point to bytes
11482  if (codepoint < 0x80)
11483  {
11484  // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
11485  add(codepoint);
11486  }
11487  else if (codepoint <= 0x7ff)
11488  {
11489  // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
11490  add(0xC0 | (codepoint >> 6));
11491  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
11492  }
11493  else if (codepoint <= 0xffff)
11494  {
11495  // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
11496  add(0xE0 | (codepoint >> 12));
11497  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F));
11498  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
11499  }
11500  else
11501  {
11502  // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
11503  add(0xF0 | (codepoint >> 18));
11504  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 12) & 0x3F));
11505  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F));
11506  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
11507  }
11508 
11509  break;
11510  }
11511 
11512  // other characters after escape
11513  default:
11514  error_message = "invalid string: forbidden character after backslash";
11515  return token_type::parse_error;
11516  }
11517 
11518  break;
11519  }
11520 
11521  // invalid control characters
11522  case 0x00:
11523  case 0x01:
11524  case 0x02:
11525  case 0x03:
11526  case 0x04:
11527  case 0x05:
11528  case 0x06:
11529  case 0x07:
11530  case 0x08:
11531  case 0x09:
11532  case 0x0a:
11533  case 0x0b:
11534  case 0x0c:
11535  case 0x0d:
11536  case 0x0e:
11537  case 0x0f:
11538  case 0x10:
11539  case 0x11:
11540  case 0x12:
11541  case 0x13:
11542  case 0x14:
11543  case 0x15:
11544  case 0x16:
11545  case 0x17:
11546  case 0x18:
11547  case 0x19:
11548  case 0x1a:
11549  case 0x1b:
11550  case 0x1c:
11551  case 0x1d:
11552  case 0x1e:
11553  case 0x1f:
11554  {
11555  error_message = "invalid string: control character " + codepoint_to_string(current) + " must be escaped";
11556  return token_type::parse_error;
11557  }
11558 
11559  // U+0020..U+007F (except U+0022 (quote) and U+005C (backspace))
11560  case 0x20:
11561  case 0x21:
11562  case 0x23:
11563  case 0x24:
11564  case 0x25:
11565  case 0x26:
11566  case 0x27:
11567  case 0x28:
11568  case 0x29:
11569  case 0x2a:
11570  case 0x2b:
11571  case 0x2c:
11572  case 0x2d:
11573  case 0x2e:
11574  case 0x2f:
11575  case 0x30:
11576  case 0x31:
11577  case 0x32:
11578  case 0x33:

11580  case 0x35:
11581  case 0x36:
11582  case 0x37:
11583  case 0x38:

11588  case 0x3d:
11589  case 0x3e:

11591  case 0x40:

11594  case 0x43:

11597  case 0x46:

11661  case 0xc3:
11662  case 0xc4:
11663  case 0xc5:
11664  case 0xc6:
11665  case 0xc7:
11666  case 0xc8:
11667  case 0xc9:
11668  case 0xca:
11669  case 0xcb:
11670  case 0xcc:
11671  case 0xcd:
11672  case 0xce:
11673  case 0xcf:
11674  case 0xd0:
11675  case 0xd1:
11676  case 0xd2:
11677  case 0xd3:
11678  case 0xd4:
11679  case 0xd5:
11680  case 0xd6:
11681  case 0xd7:
11682  case 0xd8:
11683  case 0xd9:
11684  case 0xda:
11685  case 0xdb:
11686  case 0xdc:
11687  case 0xdd:
11688  case 0xde:
11689  case 0xdf:
11690  {
11691  add(current);
11692  get();
11693  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11694  {
11695  add(current);
11696  continue;
11697  }
11698 
11699  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
11700  return token_type::parse_error;
11701  }
11702 
11703  // U+0800..U+0FFF: bytes E0 A0..BF 80..BF
11704  case 0xe0:
11705  {
11706  add(current);
11707  get();
11708  if (JSON_LIKELY(0xa0 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11709  {
11710  add(current);
11711  get();
11712  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11713  {
11714  add(current);
11715  continue;
11716  }
11717  }
11718 
11719  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
11720  return token_type::parse_error;
11721  }
11722 
11723  // U+1000..U+CFFF: bytes E1..EC 80..BF 80..BF
11724  // U+E000..U+FFFF: bytes EE..EF 80..BF 80..BF
11725  case 0xe1:
11726  case 0xe2:
11727  case 0xe3:
11728  case 0xe4:
11729  case 0xe5:
11730  case 0xe6:
11731  case 0xe7:
11732  case 0xe8:
11733  case 0xe9:
11734  case 0xea:
11735  case 0xeb:
11736  case 0xec:
11737  case 0xee:
11738  case 0xef:
11739  {
11740  add(current);
11741  get();
11742  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11743  {
11744  add(current);
11745  get();
11746  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11747  {
11748  add(current);
11749  continue;
11750  }
11751  }
11752 
11753  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
11754  return token_type::parse_error;
11755  }
11756 
11757  // U+D000..U+D7FF: bytes ED 80..9F 80..BF
11758  case 0xed:
11759  {
11760  add(current);
11761  get();
11762  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0x9f))
11763  {
11764  add(current);
11765  get();
11766  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11767  {
11768  add(current);
11769  continue;
11770  }
11771  }
11772 
11773  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
11774  return token_type::parse_error;
11775  }
11776 
11777  // U+10000..U+3FFFF F0 90..BF 80..BF 80..BF
11778  case 0xf0:
11779  {
11780  add(current);
11781  get();
11782  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x90 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11783  {
11784  add(current);
11785  get();
11786  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11787  {
11788  add(current);
11789  get();
11790  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11791  {
11792  add(current);
11793  continue;
11794  }
11795  }
11796  }
11797 
11798  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
11799  return token_type::parse_error;
11800  }
11801 
11802  // U+40000..U+FFFFF F1..F3 80..BF 80..BF 80..BF
11803  case 0xf1:
11804  case 0xf2:
11805  case 0xf3:
11806  {
11807  add(current);
11808  get();
11809  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11810  {
11811  add(current);
11812  get();
11813  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11814  {
11815  add(current);
11816  get();
11817  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11818  {
11819  add(current);
11820  continue;
11821  }
11822  }
11823  }
11824 
11825  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
11826  return token_type::parse_error;
11827  }
11828 
11829  // U+100000..U+10FFFF F4 80..8F 80..BF 80..BF
11830  case 0xf4:
11831  {
11832  add(current);
11833  get();
11834  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0x8f))
11835  {
11836  add(current);
11837  get();
11838  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11839  {
11840  add(current);
11841  get();
11842  if (JSON_LIKELY(0x80 <= current and current <= 0xbf))
11843  {
11844  add(current);
11845  continue;
11846  }
11847  }
11848  }
11849 
11850  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
11851  return token_type::parse_error;
11852  }
11853 
11854  // remaining bytes (80..C1 and F5..FF) are ill-formed
11855  default:
11856  {
11857  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
11858  return token_type::parse_error;
11859  }
11860  }
11861  }
11862  }
11863 
11864  static void strtof(float& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
11865  {
11866  f = std::strtof(str, endptr);
11867  }
11868 
11869  static void strtof(double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
11870  {
11871  f = std::strtod(str, endptr);
11872  }
11873 
11874  static void strtof(long double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
11875  {
11876  f = std::strtold(str, endptr);
11877  }
11878 
11920  token_type scan_number()
11921  {
11922  // reset yytext to store the number's bytes
11923  reset();
11924 
11925  // the type of the parsed number; initially set to unsigned; will be
11926  // changed if minus sign, decimal point or exponent is read
11927  token_type number_type = token_type::value_unsigned;
11928 
11929  // state (init): we just found out we need to scan a number
11930  switch (current)
11931  {
11932  case '-':
11933  {
11934  add(current);
11935  goto scan_number_minus;
11936  }
11937 
11938  case '0':
11939  {
11940  add(current);
11941  goto scan_number_zero;
11942  }
11943 
11944  case '1':
11945  case '2':
11946  case '3':
11947  case '4':
11948  case '5':
11949  case '6':
11950  case '7':
11951  case '8':
11952  case '9':
11953  {
11954  add(current);
11955  goto scan_number_any1;
11956  }
11957 
11958  default:
11959  {
11960  // all other characters are rejected outside scan_number()
11961  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
11962  }
11963  }
11964 
11965 scan_number_minus:
11966  // state: we just parsed a leading minus sign
11967  number_type = token_type::value_integer;
11968  switch (get())
11969  {
11970  case '0':
11971  {
11972  add(current);
11973  goto scan_number_zero;
11974  }
11975 
11976  case '1':
11977  case '2':
11978  case '3':
11979  case '4':
11980  case '5':
11981  case '6':
11982  case '7':
11983  case '8':
11984  case '9':
11985  {
11986  add(current);
11987  goto scan_number_any1;
11988  }
11989 
11990  default:
11991  {
11992  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '-'";
11993  return token_type::parse_error;
11994  }
11995  }
11996 
11997 scan_number_zero:
11998  // state: we just parse a zero (maybe with a leading minus sign)
11999  switch (get())
12000  {
12001  case '.':
12002  {
12003  add(decimal_point_char);
12004  goto scan_number_decimal1;
12005  }
12006 
12007  case 'e':
12008  case 'E':
12009  {
12010  add(current);
12011  goto scan_number_exponent;
12012  }
12013 
12014  default:
12015  {
12016  goto scan_number_done;
12017  }
12018  }
12019 
12020 scan_number_any1:
12021  // state: we just parsed a number 0-9 (maybe with a leading minus sign)
12022  switch (get())
12023  {
12024  case '0':
12025  case '1':
12026  case '2':
12027  case '3':
12028  case '4':
12029  case '5':
12030  case '6':
12031  case '7':
12032  case '8':
12033  case '9':
12034  {
12035  add(current);
12036  goto scan_number_any1;
12037  }
12038 
12039  case '.':
12040  {
12041  add(decimal_point_char);
12042  goto scan_number_decimal1;
12043  }
12044 
12045  case 'e':
12046  case 'E':
12047  {
12048  add(current);
12049  goto scan_number_exponent;
12050  }
12051 
12052  default:
12053  {
12054  goto scan_number_done;
12055  }
12056  }
12057 
12058 scan_number_decimal1:
12059  // state: we just parsed a decimal point
12060  number_type = token_type::value_float;
12061  switch (get())
12062  {
12063  case '0':
12064  case '1':
12065  case '2':
12066  case '3':
12067  case '4':
12068  case '5':
12069  case '6':
12070  case '7':
12071  case '8':
12072  case '9':
12073  {
12074  add(current);
12075  goto scan_number_decimal2;
12076  }
12077 
12078  default:
12079  {
12080  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '.'";
12081  return token_type::parse_error;
12082  }
12083  }
12084 
12085 scan_number_decimal2:
12086  // we just parsed at least one number after a decimal point
12087  switch (get())
12088  {
12089  case '0':
12090  case '1':
12091  case '2':
12092  case '3':
12093  case '4':
12094  case '5':
12095  case '6':
12096  case '7':
12097  case '8':
12098  case '9':
12099  {
12100  add(current);
12101  goto scan_number_decimal2;
12102  }
12103 
12104  case 'e':
12105  case 'E':
12106  {
12107  add(current);
12108  goto scan_number_exponent;
12109  }
12110 
12111  default:
12112  {
12113  goto scan_number_done;
12114  }
12115  }
12116 
12117 scan_number_exponent:
12118  // we just parsed an exponent
12119  number_type = token_type::value_float;
12120  switch (get())
12121  {
12122  case '+':
12123  case '-':
12124  {
12125  add(current);
12126  goto scan_number_sign;
12127  }
12128 
12129  case '0':
12130  case '1':
12131  case '2':
12132  case '3':
12133  case '4':
12134  case '5':
12135  case '6':
12136  case '7':
12137  case '8':
12138  case '9':
12139  {
12140  add(current);
12141  goto scan_number_any2;
12142  }
12143 
12144  default:
12145  {
12146  error_message = "invalid number; expected '+', '-', or digit after exponent";
12147  return token_type::parse_error;
12148  }
12149  }
12150 
12151 scan_number_sign:
12152  // we just parsed an exponent sign
12153  switch (get())
12154  {
12155  case '0':
12156  case '1':
12157  case '2':
12158  case '3':
12159  case '4':
12160  case '5':
12161  case '6':
12162  case '7':
12163  case '8':
12164  case '9':
12165  {
12166  add(current);
12167  goto scan_number_any2;
12168  }
12169 
12170  default:
12171  {
12172  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after exponent sign";
12173  return token_type::parse_error;
12174  }
12175  }
12176 
12177 scan_number_any2:
12178  // we just parsed a number after the exponent or exponent sign
12179  switch (get())
12180  {
12181  case '0':
12182  case '1':
12183  case '2':
12184  case '3':
12185  case '4':
12186  case '5':
12187  case '6':
12188  case '7':
12189  case '8':
12190  case '9':
12191  {
12192  add(current);
12193  goto scan_number_any2;
12194  }
12195 
12196  default:
12197  {
12198  goto scan_number_done;
12199  }
12200  }
12201 
12202 scan_number_done:
12203  // unget the character after the number (we only read it to know
12204  // that we are done scanning a number)
12205  --chars_read;
12206  next_unget = true;
12207 
12208  // terminate token
12209  add('\0');
12210  --yylen;
12211 
12212  // try to parse integers first and fall back to floats
12213  if (number_type == token_type::value_unsigned)
12214  {
12215  char* endptr = nullptr;
12216  errno = 0;
12217  const auto x = std::strtoull(yytext.data(), &endptr, 10);
12218 
12219  // we checked the number format before
12220  assert(endptr == yytext.data() + yylen);
12221 
12222  if (errno == 0)
12223  {
12224  value_unsigned = static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(x);
12225  if (value_unsigned == x)
12226  {
12227  return token_type::value_unsigned;
12228  }
12229  }
12230  }
12231  else if (number_type == token_type::value_integer)
12232  {
12233  char* endptr = nullptr;
12234  errno = 0;
12235  const auto x = std::strtoll(yytext.data(), &endptr, 10);
12236 
12237  // we checked the number format before
12238  assert(endptr == yytext.data() + yylen);
12239 
12240  if (errno == 0)
12241  {
12242  value_integer = static_cast<number_integer_t>(x);
12243  if (value_integer == x)
12244  {
12245  return token_type::value_integer;
12246  }
12247  }
12248  }
12249 
12250  // this code is reached if we parse a floating-point number or if
12251  // an integer conversion above failed
12252  strtof(value_float, yytext.data(), nullptr);
12253  return token_type::value_float;
12254  }
12255 
12256  token_type scan_true()
12257  {
12258  assert(current == 't');
12259  if (JSON_LIKELY((get() == 'r' and get() == 'u' and get() == 'e')))
12260  {
12261  return token_type::literal_true;
12262  }
12263 
12264  error_message = "invalid literal; expected 'true'";
12265  return token_type::parse_error;
12266  }
12267 
12268  token_type scan_false()
12269  {
12270  assert(current == 'f');
12271  if (JSON_LIKELY((get() == 'a' and get() == 'l' and get() == 's' and get() == 'e')))
12272  {
12273  return token_type::literal_false;
12274  }
12275 
12276  error_message = "invalid literal; expected 'false'";
12277  return token_type::parse_error;
12278  }
12279 
12280  token_type scan_null()
12281  {
12282  assert(current == 'n');
12283  if (JSON_LIKELY((get() == 'u' and get() == 'l' and get() == 'l')))
12284  {
12285  return token_type::literal_null;
12286  }
12287 
12288  error_message = "invalid literal; expected 'null'";
12289  return token_type::parse_error;
12290  }
12291 
12293  // input management
12295 
12297  void reset() noexcept
12298  {
12299  yylen = 0;
12300  start_pos = chars_read - 1;
12301  }
12302 
12304  int get()
12305  {
12306  ++chars_read;
12307  return next_unget
12308  ? (next_unget = false, current)
12309  : (current = ia->get_character());
12310  }
12311 
12313  void add(int c)
12314  {
12315  // resize yytext if necessary; this condition is deemed unlikely,
12316  // because we start with a 1024-byte buffer
12317  if (JSON_UNLIKELY((yylen + 1 > yytext.capacity())))
12318  {
12319  yytext.resize(2 * yytext.capacity(), '\0');
12320  }
12321  yytext[yylen++] = static_cast<char>(c);
12322  }
12323 
12324  public:
12326  // value getters
12328 
12330  constexpr number_integer_t get_number_integer() const noexcept
12331  {
12332  return value_integer;
12333  }
12334 
12336  constexpr number_unsigned_t get_number_unsigned() const noexcept
12337  {
12338  return value_unsigned;
12339  }
12340 
12342  constexpr number_float_t get_number_float() const noexcept
12343  {
12344  return value_float;
12345  }
12346 
12348  const std::string get_string()
12349  {
12350  // yytext cannot be returned as char*, because it may contain a
12351  // null byte (parsed as "\u0000")
12352  return std::string(yytext.data(), yylen);
12353  }
12354 
12356  // diagnostics
12358 
12360  constexpr size_t get_position() const noexcept
12361  {
12362  return chars_read;
12363  }
12364 
12366  std::string get_token_string() const
12367  {
12368  // get the raw byte sequence of the last token
12369  std::string s = ia->read(start_pos, chars_read - start_pos);
12370 
12371  // escape control characters
12372  std::string result;
12373  for (auto c : s)
12374  {
12375  if (c == '\0' or c == std::char_traits<char>::eof())
12376  {
12377  // ignore EOF
12378  continue;
12379  }
12380  else if ('\x00' <= c and c <= '\x1f')
12381  {
12382  // escape control characters
12383  result += "<" + codepoint_to_string(c) + ">";
12384  }
12385  else
12386  {
12387  // add character as is
12388  result.append(1, c);
12389  }
12390  }
12391 
12392  return result;
12393  }
12394 
12396  const std::string& get_error_message() const noexcept
12397  {
12398  return error_message;
12399  }
12400 
12402  // actual scanner
12404 
12405  token_type scan()
12406  {
12407  // read next character and ignore whitespace
12408  do
12409  {
12410  get();
12411  }
12412  while (current == ' ' or current == '\t' or current == '\n' or current == '\r');
12413 
12414  switch (current)
12415  {
12416  // structural characters
12417  case '[':
12418  return token_type::begin_array;
12419  case ']':
12420  return token_type::end_array;
12421  case '{':
12422  return token_type::begin_object;
12423  case '}':
12424  return token_type::end_object;
12425  case ':':
12426  return token_type::name_separator;
12427  case ',':
12428  return token_type::value_separator;
12429 
12430  // literals
12431  case 't':
12432  return scan_true();
12433  case 'f':
12434  return scan_false();
12435  case 'n':
12436  return scan_null();
12437 
12438  // string
12439  case '\"':
12440  return scan_string();
12441 
12442  // number
12443  case '-':
12444  case '0':
12445  case '1':
12446  case '2':
12447  case '3':
12448  case '4':
12449  case '5':
12450  case '6':
12451  case '7':
12452  case '8':
12453  case '9':
12454  return scan_number();
12455 
12456  // end of input (the null byte is needed when parsing from
12457  // string literals)
12458  case '\0':
12459  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
12460  return token_type::end_of_input;
12461 
12462  // error
12463  default:
12464  error_message = "invalid literal";
12465  return token_type::parse_error;
12466  }
12467  }
12468 
12469  private:
12471  input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
12472 
12474  int current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
12475 
12477  bool next_unget = false;
12478 
12480  size_t chars_read = 0;
12482  size_t start_pos = 0;
12483 
12485  std::vector<char> yytext = std::vector<char>(1024, '\0');
12487  size_t yylen = 0;
12488 
12490  std::string error_message = "";
12491 
12492  // number values
12493  number_integer_t value_integer = 0;
12494  number_unsigned_t value_unsigned = 0;
12495  number_float_t value_float = 0;
12496 
12498  const char decimal_point_char = '.';
12499  };
12500 
12506  class parser
12507  {
12508  public:
12510  explicit parser(input_adapter_t adapter,
12511  const parser_callback_t cb = nullptr)
12512  : callback(cb), m_lexer(adapter)
12513  {}
12514 
12525  basic_json parse(const bool strict = true)
12526  {
12527  // read first token
12528  get_token();
12529 
12530  basic_json result = parse_internal(true);
12531  result.assert_invariant();
12532 
12533  if (strict)
12534  {
12535  expect(lexer::token_type::end_of_input);
12536  }
12537 
12538  // return parser result and replace it with null in case the
12539  // top-level value was discarded by the callback function
12540  return result.is_discarded() ? basic_json() : std::move(result);
12541  }
12542 
12549  bool accept(const bool strict = true)
12550  {
12551  // read first token
12552  get_token();
12553 
12554  if (not accept_internal())
12555  {
12556  return false;
12557  }
12558 
12559  if (strict and last_token != lexer::token_type::end_of_input)
12560  {
12561  return false;
12562  }
12563 
12564  return true;
12565  }
12566 
12567  private:
12574  basic_json parse_internal(bool keep)
12575  {
12576  auto result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
12577 
12578  switch (last_token)
12579  {
12580  case lexer::token_type::begin_object:
12581  {
12582  if (keep and (not callback
12583  or ((keep = callback(depth++, parse_event_t::object_start, result)) != 0)))
12584  {
12585  // explicitly set result to object to cope with {}
12586  result.m_type = value_t::object;
12587  result.m_value = value_t::object;
12588  }
12589 
12590  // read next token
12591  get_token();
12592 
12593  // closing } -> we are done
12594  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::end_object)
12595  {
12596  get_token();
12597  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::object_end, result))
12598  {
12599  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
12600  }
12601  return result;
12602  }
12603 
12604  // parse values
12605  while (true)
12606  {
12607  // store key
12608  expect(lexer::token_type::value_string);
12609  const auto key = m_lexer.get_string();
12610 
12611  bool keep_tag = false;
12612  if (keep)
12613  {
12614  if (callback)
12615  {
12616  basic_json k(key);
12617  keep_tag = callback(depth, parse_event_t::key, k);
12618  }
12619  else
12620  {
12621  keep_tag = true;
12622  }
12623  }
12624 
12625  // parse separator (:)
12626  get_token();
12627  expect(lexer::token_type::name_separator);
12628 
12629  // parse and add value
12630  get_token();
12631  auto value = parse_internal(keep);
12632  if (keep and keep_tag and not value.is_discarded())
12633  {
12634  result[key] = std::move(value);
12635  }
12636 
12637  // comma -> next value
12638  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::value_separator)
12639  {
12640  get_token();
12641  continue;
12642  }
12643 
12644  // closing }
12645  expect(lexer::token_type::end_object);
12646  get_token();
12647  break;
12648  }
12649 
12650  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::object_end, result))
12651  {
12652  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
12653  }
12654 
12655  return result;
12656  }
12657 
12658  case lexer::token_type::begin_array:
12659  {
12660  if (keep and (not callback
12661  or ((keep = callback(depth++, parse_event_t::array_start, result)) != 0)))
12662  {
12663  // explicitly set result to object to cope with []
12664  result.m_type = value_t::array;
12665  result.m_value = value_t::array;
12666  }
12667 
12668  // read next token
12669  get_token();
12670 
12671  // closing ] -> we are done
12672  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::end_array)
12673  {
12674  get_token();
12675  if (callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::array_end, result))
12676  {
12677  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
12678  }
12679  return result;
12680  }
12681 
12682  // parse values
12683  while (true)
12684  {
12685  // parse value
12686  auto value = parse_internal(keep);
12687  if (keep and not value.is_discarded())
12688  {
12689  result.push_back(std::move(value));
12690  }
12691 
12692  // comma -> next value
12693  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::value_separator)
12694  {
12695  get_token();
12696  continue;
12697  }
12698 
12699  // closing ]
12700  expect(lexer::token_type::end_array);
12701  get_token();
12702  break;
12703  }
12704 
12705  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::array_end, result))
12706  {
12707  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
12708  }
12709 
12710  return result;
12711  }
12712 
12713  case lexer::token_type::literal_null:
12714  {
12715  result.m_type = value_t::null;
12716  get_token();
12717  break;
12718  }
12719 
12720  case lexer::token_type::value_string:
12721  {
12722  result = basic_json(m_lexer.get_string());
12723  get_token();
12724  break;
12725  }
12726 
12727  case lexer::token_type::literal_true:
12728  {
12729  result.m_type = value_t::boolean;
12730  result.m_value = true;
12731  get_token();
12732  break;
12733  }
12734 
12735  case lexer::token_type::literal_false:
12736  {
12737  result.m_type = value_t::boolean;
12738  result.m_value = false;
12739  get_token();
12740  break;
12741  }
12742 
12743  case lexer::token_type::value_unsigned:
12744  {
12745  result.m_type = value_t::number_unsigned;
12746  result.m_value = m_lexer.get_number_unsigned();
12747  get_token();
12748  break;
12749  }
12750 
12751  case lexer::token_type::value_integer:
12752  {
12753  result.m_type = value_t::number_integer;
12754  result.m_value = m_lexer.get_number_integer();
12755  get_token();
12756  break;
12757  }
12758 
12759  case lexer::token_type::value_float:
12760  {
12761  result.m_type = value_t::number_float;
12762  result.m_value = m_lexer.get_number_float();
12763 
12764  // throw in case of infinity or NAN
12765  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not std::isfinite(result.m_value.number_float)))
12766  {
12767  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(406, "number overflow parsing '" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'"));
12768  }
12769 
12770  get_token();
12771  break;
12772  }
12773 
12774  default:
12775  {
12776  // the last token was unexpected
12777  unexpect(last_token);
12778  }
12779  }
12780 
12781  if (keep and callback and not callback(depth, parse_event_t::value, result))
12782  {
12783  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
12784  }
12785  return result;
12786  }
12787 
12791  bool accept_internal()
12792  {
12793  switch (last_token)
12794  {
12795  case lexer::token_type::begin_object:
12796  {
12797  // read next token
12798  get_token();
12799 
12800  // closing } -> we are done
12801  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::end_object)
12802  {
12803  get_token();
12804  return true;
12805  }
12806 
12807  // parse values
12808  while (true)
12809  {
12810  // parse key
12811  if (last_token != lexer::token_type::value_string)
12812  {
12813  return false;
12814  }
12815 
12816  // parse separator (:)
12817  get_token();
12818  if (last_token != lexer::token_type::name_separator)
12819  {
12820  return false;
12821  }
12822 
12823  // parse value
12824  get_token();
12825  if (not accept_internal())
12826  {
12827  return false;
12828  }
12829 
12830  // comma -> next value
12831  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::value_separator)
12832  {
12833  get_token();
12834  continue;
12835  }
12836 
12837  // closing }
12838  if (last_token != lexer::token_type::end_object)
12839  {
12840  return false;
12841  }
12842 
12843  get_token();
12844  return true;
12845  }
12846  }
12847 
12848  case lexer::token_type::begin_array:
12849  {
12850  // read next token
12851  get_token();
12852 
12853  // closing ] -> we are done
12854  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::end_array)
12855  {
12856  get_token();
12857  return true;
12858  }
12859 
12860  // parse values
12861  while (true)
12862  {
12863  // parse value
12864  if (not accept_internal())
12865  {
12866  return false;
12867  }
12868 
12869  // comma -> next value
12870  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::value_separator)
12871  {
12872  get_token();
12873  continue;
12874  }
12875 
12876  // closing ]
12877  if (last_token != lexer::token_type::end_array)
12878  {
12879  return false;
12880  }
12881 
12882  get_token();
12883  return true;
12884  }
12885  }
12886 
12887  case lexer::token_type::literal_null:
12888  case lexer::token_type::value_string:
12889  case lexer::token_type::literal_true:
12890  case lexer::token_type::literal_false:
12891  case lexer::token_type::value_unsigned:
12892  case lexer::token_type::value_integer:
12893  case lexer::token_type::value_float:
12894  {
12895  get_token();
12896  return true;
12897  }
12898 
12899  default:
12900  {
12901  // the last token was unexpected
12902  return false;
12903  }
12904  }
12905  }
12906 
12908  typename lexer::token_type get_token()
12909  {
12910  last_token = m_lexer.scan();
12911  return last_token;
12912  }
12913 
12917  void expect(typename lexer::token_type t) const
12918  {
12919  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(t != last_token))
12920  {
12921  std::string error_msg = "syntax error - ";
12922  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::parse_error)
12923  {
12924  error_msg += m_lexer.get_error_message() + "; last read: '" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'";
12925  }
12926  else
12927  {
12928  error_msg += "unexpected " + std::string(lexer::token_type_name(last_token));
12929  }
12930 
12931  error_msg += "; expected " + std::string(lexer::token_type_name(t));
12932  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), error_msg));
12933  }
12934  }
12935 
12939  void unexpect(typename lexer::token_type t) const
12940  {
12941  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(t == last_token))
12942  {
12943  std::string error_msg = "syntax error - ";
12944  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::parse_error)
12945  {
12946  error_msg += m_lexer.get_error_message() + "; last read '" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'";
12947  }
12948  else
12949  {
12950  error_msg += "unexpected " + std::string(lexer::token_type_name(last_token));
12951  }
12952 
12953  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), error_msg));
12954  }
12955  }
12956 
12957  private:
12959  int depth = 0;
12961  const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
12963  typename lexer::token_type last_token = lexer::token_type::uninitialized;
12965  lexer m_lexer;
12966  };
12967 
12968  public:
12980  class json_pointer
12981  {
12983  friend class basic_json;
12984 
12985  public:
13008  explicit json_pointer(const std::string& s = "")
13009  : reference_tokens(split(s))
13010  {}
13011 
13027  std::string to_string() const noexcept
13028  {
13029  return std::accumulate(reference_tokens.begin(),
13030  reference_tokens.end(), std::string{},
13031  [](const std::string & a, const std::string & b)
13032  {
13033  return a + "/" + escape(b);
13034  });
13035  }
13036 
13038  operator std::string() const
13039  {
13040  return to_string();
13041  }
13042 
13043  private:
13048  std::string pop_back()
13049  {
13050  if (is_root())
13051  {
13052  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
13053  }
13054 
13055  auto last = reference_tokens.back();
13056  reference_tokens.pop_back();
13057  return last;
13058  }
13059 
13061  bool is_root() const
13062  {
13063  return reference_tokens.empty();
13064  }
13065 
13066  json_pointer top() const
13067  {
13068  if (is_root())
13069  {
13070  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
13071  }
13072 
13073  json_pointer result = *this;
13074  result.reference_tokens = {reference_tokens[0]};
13075  return result;
13076  }
13077 
13086  reference get_and_create(reference j) const
13087  {
13088  pointer result = &j;
13089 
13090  // in case no reference tokens exist, return a reference to the
13091  // JSON value j which will be overwritten by a primitive value
13092  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
13093  {
13094  switch (result->m_type)
13095  {
13096  case value_t::null:
13097  {
13098  if (reference_token == "0")
13099  {
13100  // start a new array if reference token is 0
13101  result = &result->operator[](0);
13102  }
13103  else
13104  {
13105  // start a new object otherwise
13106  result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
13107  }
13108  break;
13109  }
13110 
13111  case value_t::object:
13112  {
13113  // create an entry in the object
13114  result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
13115  break;
13116  }
13117 
13118  case value_t::array:
13119  {
13120  // create an entry in the array
13121  JSON_TRY
13122  {
13123  result = &result->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(std::stoi(reference_token)));
13124  }
13125  JSON_CATCH (std::invalid_argument&)
13126  {
13127  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
13128  }
13129  break;
13130  }
13131 
13132  /*
13133  The following code is only reached if there exists a
13134  reference token _and_ the current value is primitive. In
13135  this case, we have an error situation, because primitive
13136  values may only occur as single value; that is, with an
13137  empty list of reference tokens.
13138  */
13139  default:
13140  {
13141  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(313, "invalid value to unflatten"));
13142  }
13143  }
13144  }
13145 
13146  return *result;
13147  }
13148 
13168  reference get_unchecked(pointer ptr) const
13169  {
13170  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
13171  {
13172  // convert null values to arrays or objects before continuing
13173  if (ptr->m_type == value_t::null)
13174  {
13175  // check if reference token is a number
13176  const bool nums = std::all_of(reference_token.begin(),
13177  reference_token.end(),
13178  [](const char x)
13179  {
13180  return (x >= '0' and x <= '9');
13181  });
13182 
13183  // change value to array for numbers or "-" or to object
13184  // otherwise
13185  if (nums or reference_token == "-")
13186  {
13187  *ptr = value_t::array;
13188  }
13189  else
13190  {
13191  *ptr = value_t::object;
13192  }
13193  }
13194 
13195  switch (ptr->m_type)
13196  {
13197  case value_t::object:
13198  {
13199  // use unchecked object access
13200  ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
13201  break;
13202  }
13203 
13204  case value_t::array:
13205  {
13206  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
13207  if (reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0')
13208  {
13209  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(106, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' must not begin with '0'"));
13210  }
13211 
13212  if (reference_token == "-")
13213  {
13214  // explicitly treat "-" as index beyond the end
13215  ptr = &ptr->operator[](ptr->m_value.array->size());
13216  }
13217  else
13218  {
13219  // convert array index to number; unchecked access
13220  JSON_TRY
13221  {
13222  ptr = &ptr->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(std::stoi(reference_token)));
13223  }
13224  JSON_CATCH (std::invalid_argument&)
13225  {
13226  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
13227  }
13228  }
13229  break;
13230  }
13231 
13232  default:
13233  {
13234  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
13235  }
13236  }
13237  }
13238 
13239  return *ptr;
13240  }
13241 
13248  reference get_checked(pointer ptr) const
13249  {
13250  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
13251  {
13252  switch (ptr->m_type)
13253  {
13254  case value_t::object:
13255  {
13256  // note: at performs range check
13257  ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
13258  break;
13259  }
13260 
13261  case value_t::array:
13262  {
13263  if (reference_token == "-")
13264  {
13265  // "-" always fails the range check
13266  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(402, "array index '-' (" +
13267  std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
13268  ") is out of range"));
13269  }
13270 
13271  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
13272  if (reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0')
13273  {
13274  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(106, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' must not begin with '0'"));
13275  }
13276 
13277  // note: at performs range check
13278  JSON_TRY
13279  {
13280  ptr = &ptr->at(static_cast<size_type>(std::stoi(reference_token)));
13281  }
13282  JSON_CATCH (std::invalid_argument&)
13283  {
13284  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
13285  }
13286  break;
13287  }
13288 
13289  default:
13290  {
13291  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
13292  }
13293  }
13294  }
13295 
13296  return *ptr;
13297  }
13298 
13312  const_reference get_unchecked(const_pointer ptr) const
13313  {
13314  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
13315  {
13316  switch (ptr->m_type)
13317  {
13318  case value_t::object:
13319  {
13320  // use unchecked object access
13321  ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
13322  break;
13323  }
13324 
13325  case value_t::array:
13326  {
13327  if (reference_token == "-")
13328  {
13329  // "-" cannot be used for const access
13330  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(402, "array index '-' (" +
13331  std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
13332  ") is out of range"));
13333  }
13334 
13335  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
13336  if (reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0')
13337  {
13338  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(106, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' must not begin with '0'"));
13339  }
13340 
13341  // use unchecked array access
13342  JSON_TRY
13343  {
13344  ptr = &ptr->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(std::stoi(reference_token)));
13345  }
13346  JSON_CATCH (std::invalid_argument&)
13347  {
13348  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
13349  }
13350  break;
13351  }
13352 
13353  default:
13354  {
13355  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
13356  }
13357  }
13358  }
13359 
13360  return *ptr;
13361  }
13362 
13369  const_reference get_checked(const_pointer ptr) const
13370  {
13371  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
13372  {
13373  switch (ptr->m_type)
13374  {
13375  case value_t::object:
13376  {
13377  // note: at performs range check
13378  ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
13379  break;
13380  }
13381 
13382  case value_t::array:
13383  {
13384  if (reference_token == "-")
13385  {
13386  // "-" always fails the range check
13387  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(402, "array index '-' (" +
13388  std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
13389  ") is out of range"));
13390  }
13391 
13392  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
13393  if (reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0')
13394  {
13395  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(106, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' must not begin with '0'"));
13396  }
13397 
13398  // note: at performs range check
13399  JSON_TRY
13400  {
13401  ptr = &ptr->at(static_cast<size_type>(std::stoi(reference_token)));
13402  }
13403  JSON_CATCH (std::invalid_argument&)
13404  {
13405  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
13406  }
13407  break;
13408  }
13409 
13410  default:
13411  {
13412  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
13413  }
13414  }
13415  }
13416 
13417  return *ptr;
13418  }
13419 
13429  static std::vector<std::string> split(const std::string& reference_string)
13430  {
13431  std::vector<std::string> result;
13432 
13433  // special case: empty reference string -> no reference tokens
13434  if (reference_string.empty())
13435  {
13436  return result;
13437  }
13438 
13439  // check if nonempty reference string begins with slash
13440  if (reference_string[0] != '/')
13441  {
13442  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(107, 1, "JSON pointer must be empty or begin with '/' - was: '" + reference_string + "'"));
13443  }
13444 
13445  // extract the reference tokens:
13446  // - slash: position of the last read slash (or end of string)
13447  // - start: position after the previous slash
13448  for (
13449  // search for the first slash after the first character
13450  size_t slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', 1),
13451  // set the beginning of the first reference token
13452  start = 1;
13453  // we can stop if start == string::npos+1 = 0
13454  start != 0;
13455  // set the beginning of the next reference token
13456  // (will eventually be 0 if slash == std::string::npos)
13457  start = slash + 1,
13458  // find next slash
13459  slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', start))
13460  {
13461  // use the text between the beginning of the reference token
13462  // (start) and the last slash (slash).
13463  auto reference_token = reference_string.substr(start, slash - start);
13464 
13465  // check reference tokens are properly escaped
13466  for (size_t pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~');
13467  pos != std::string::npos;
13468  pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~', pos + 1))
13469  {
13470  assert(reference_token[pos] == '~');
13471 
13472  // ~ must be followed by 0 or 1
13473  if (pos == reference_token.size() - 1 or
13474  (reference_token[pos + 1] != '0' and
13475  reference_token[pos + 1] != '1'))
13476  {
13477  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(108, 0, "escape character '~' must be followed with '0' or '1'"));
13478  }
13479  }
13480 
13481  // finally, store the reference token
13482  unescape(reference_token);
13483  result.push_back(reference_token);
13484  }
13485 
13486  return result;
13487  }
13488 
13502  static void replace_substring(std::string& s,
13503  const std::string& f,
13504  const std::string& t)
13505  {
13506  assert(not f.empty());
13507 
13508  for (
13509  size_t pos = s.find(f); // find first occurrence of f
13510  pos != std::string::npos; // make sure f was found
13511  s.replace(pos, f.size(), t), // replace with t
13512  pos = s.find(f, pos + t.size()) // find next occurrence of f
13513  );
13514  }
13515 
13517  static std::string escape(std::string s)
13518  {
13519  // escape "~"" to "~0" and "/" to "~1"
13520  replace_substring(s, "~", "~0");
13521  replace_substring(s, "/", "~1");
13522  return s;
13523  }
13524 
13526  static void unescape(std::string& s)
13527  {
13528  // first transform any occurrence of the sequence '~1' to '/'
13529  replace_substring(s, "~1", "/");
13530  // then transform any occurrence of the sequence '~0' to '~'
13531  replace_substring(s, "~0", "~");
13532  }
13533 
13541  static void flatten(const std::string& reference_string,
13542  const basic_json& value,
13543  basic_json& result)
13544  {
13545  switch (value.m_type)
13546  {
13547  case value_t::array:
13548  {
13549  if (value.m_value.array->empty())
13550  {
13551  // flatten empty array as null
13552  result[reference_string] = nullptr;
13553  }
13554  else
13555  {
13556  // iterate array and use index as reference string
13557  for (size_t i = 0; i < value.m_value.array->size(); ++i)
13558  {
13559  flatten(reference_string + "/" + std::to_string(i),
13560  value.m_value.array->operator[](i), result);
13561  }
13562  }
13563  break;
13564  }
13565 
13566  case value_t::object:
13567  {
13568  if (value.m_value.object->empty())
13569  {
13570  // flatten empty object as null
13571  result[reference_string] = nullptr;
13572  }
13573  else
13574  {
13575  // iterate object and use keys as reference string
13576  for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object)
13577  {
13578  flatten(reference_string + "/" + escape(element.first),
13579  element.second, result);
13580  }
13581  }
13582  break;
13583  }
13584 
13585  default:
13586  {
13587  // add primitive value with its reference string
13588  result[reference_string] = value;
13589  break;
13590  }
13591  }
13592  }
13593 
13604  static basic_json unflatten(const basic_json& value)
13605  {
13606  if (not value.is_object())
13607  {
13608  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(314, "only objects can be unflattened"));
13609  }
13610 
13611  basic_json result;
13612 
13613  // iterate the JSON object values
13614  for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object)
13615  {
13616  if (not element.second.is_primitive())
13617  {
13618  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(315, "values in object must be primitive"));
13619  }
13620 
13621  // assign value to reference pointed to by JSON pointer; Note
13622  // that if the JSON pointer is "" (i.e., points to the whole
13623  // value), function get_and_create returns a reference to
13624  // result itself. An assignment will then create a primitive
13625  // value.
13626  json_pointer(element.first).get_and_create(result) = element.second;
13627  }
13628 
13629  return result;
13630  }
13631 
13632  friend bool operator==(json_pointer const& lhs,
13633  json_pointer const& rhs) noexcept
13634  {
13635  return lhs.reference_tokens == rhs.reference_tokens;
13636  }
13637 
13638  friend bool operator!=(json_pointer const& lhs,
13639  json_pointer const& rhs) noexcept
13640  {
13641  return !(lhs == rhs);
13642  }
13643 
13645  std::vector<std::string> reference_tokens {};
13646  };
13647

13691  }

13717  {
13718  return ptr.get_unchecked(this);
13719  }

13756  reference at(const json_pointer& ptr)
13757  {
13758  return ptr.get_checked(this);
13759  }

13797  {
13798  return ptr.get_checked(this);
13799  }
