13866 
13868  // JSON Patch functions //
13870 
13873 
13921  basic_json patch(const basic_json& json_patch) const
13922  {
13923  // make a working copy to apply the patch to
13924  basic_json result = *this;
13925 
13926  // the valid JSON Patch operations
13927  enum class patch_operations {add, remove, replace, move, copy, test, invalid};
13928 
13929  const auto get_op = [](const std::string & op)
13930  {
13931  if (op == "add")
13932  {
13933  return patch_operations::add;
13934  }
13935  if (op == "remove")
13936  {
13937  return patch_operations::remove;
13938  }
13939  if (op == "replace")
13940  {
13941  return patch_operations::replace;
13942  }
13943  if (op == "move")
13944  {
13945  return patch_operations::move;
13946  }
13947  if (op == "copy")
13948  {
13949  return patch_operations::copy;
13950  }
13951  if (op == "test")
13952  {
13953  return patch_operations::test;
13954  }
13955 
13956  return patch_operations::invalid;
13957  };
13958 
13959  // wrapper for "add" operation; add value at ptr
13960  const auto operation_add = [&result](json_pointer & ptr, basic_json val)
13961  {
13962  // adding to the root of the target document means replacing it
13963  if (ptr.is_root())
13964  {
13965  result = val;
13966  }
13967  else
13968  {
13969  // make sure the top element of the pointer exists
13970  json_pointer top_pointer = ptr.top();
13971  if (top_pointer != ptr)
13972  {
13973  result.at(top_pointer);
13974  }
13975 
13976  // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
13977  const auto last_path = ptr.pop_back();
13978  basic_json& parent = result[ptr];
13979 
13980  switch (parent.m_type)
13981  {
13982  case value_t::null:
13983  case value_t::object:
13984  {
13985  // use operator[] to add value
13986  parent[last_path] = val;
13987  break;
13988  }
13989 
13990  case value_t::array:
13991  {
13992  if (last_path == "-")
13993  {
13994  // special case: append to back
13995  parent.push_back(val);
13996  }
13997  else
13998  {
13999  const auto idx = std::stoi(last_path);
14000  if (static_cast<size_type>(idx) > parent.size())
14001  {
14002  // avoid undefined behavior
14003  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(401, "array index " + std::to_string(idx) + " is out of range"));
14004  }
14005  else
14006  {
14007  // default case: insert add offset
14008  parent.insert(parent.begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(idx), val);
14009  }
14010  }
14011  break;
14012  }
14013 
14014  default:
14015  {
14016  // if there exists a parent it cannot be primitive
14017  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
14018  }
14019  }
14020  }
14021  };
14022 
14023  // wrapper for "remove" operation; remove value at ptr
14024  const auto operation_remove = [&result](json_pointer & ptr)
14025  {
14026  // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
14027  const auto last_path = ptr.pop_back();
14028  basic_json& parent = result.at(ptr);
14029 
14030  // remove child
14031  if (parent.is_object())
14032  {
14033  // perform range check
14034  auto it = parent.find(last_path);
14035  if (it != parent.end())
14036  {
14037  parent.erase(it);
14038  }
14039  else
14040  {
14041  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(403, "key '" + last_path + "' not found"));
14042  }
14043  }
14044  else if (parent.is_array())
14045  {
14046  // note erase performs range check
14047  parent.erase(static_cast<size_type>(std::stoi(last_path)));
14048  }
14049  };
14050 
14051  // type check: top level value must be an array
14052  if (not json_patch.is_array())
14053  {
14054  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(104, 0, "JSON patch must be an array of objects"));
14055  }
14056 
14057  // iterate and apply the operations
14058  for (const auto& val : json_patch)
14059  {
14060  // wrapper to get a value for an operation
14061  const auto get_value = [&val](const std::string & op,
14062  const std::string & member,
14063  bool string_type) -> basic_json&
14064  {
14065  // find value
14066  auto it = val.m_value.object->find(member);
14067 
14068  // context-sensitive error message
14069  const auto error_msg = (op == "op") ? "operation" : "operation '" + op + "'";
14070 
14071  // check if desired value is present
14072  if (it == val.m_value.object->end())
14073  {
14074  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, error_msg + " must have member '" + member + "'"));
14075  }
14076 
14077  // check if result is of type string
14078  if (string_type and not it->second.is_string())
14079  {
14080  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, error_msg + " must have string member '" + member + "'"));
14081  }
14082 
14083  // no error: return value
14084  return it->second;
14085  };
14086 
14087  // type check: every element of the array must be an object
14088  if (not val.is_object())
14089  {
14090  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(104, 0, "JSON patch must be an array of objects"));
14091  }
14092 
14093  // collect mandatory members
14094  const std::string op = get_value("op", "op", true);
14095  const std::string path = get_value(op, "path", true);
14096  json_pointer ptr(path);
14097 
14098  switch (get_op(op))
14099  {
14100  case patch_operations::add:
14101  {
14102  operation_add(ptr, get_value("add", "value", false));
14103  break;
14104  }
14105 
14106  case patch_operations::remove:
14107  {
14108  operation_remove(ptr);
14109  break;
14110  }
14111 
14112  case patch_operations::replace:
14113  {
14114  // the "path" location must exist - use at()
14115  result.at(ptr) = get_value("replace", "value", false);
14116  break;
14117  }
14118 
14119  case patch_operations::move:
14120  {
14121  const std::string from_path = get_value("move", "from", true);
14122  json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
14123 
14124  // the "from" location must exist - use at()
14125  basic_json v = result.at(from_ptr);
14126 
14127  // The move operation is functionally identical to a
14128  // "remove" operation on the "from" location, followed
14129  // immediately by an "add" operation at the target
14130  // location with the value that was just removed.
14131  operation_remove(from_ptr);
14132  operation_add(ptr, v);
14133  break;
14134  }
14135 
14136  case patch_operations::copy:
14137  {
14138  const std::string from_path = get_value("copy", "from", true);;
14139  const json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
14140 
14141  // the "from" location must exist - use at()
14142  result[ptr] = result.at(from_ptr);
14143  break;
14144  }
14145 
14146  case patch_operations::test:
14147  {
14148  bool success = false;
14149  JSON_TRY
14150  {
14151  // check if "value" matches the one at "path"
14152  // the "path" location must exist - use at()
14153  success = (result.at(ptr) == get_value("test", "value", false));
14154  }
14155  JSON_CATCH (out_of_range&)
14156  {
14157  // ignore out of range errors: success remains false
14158  }
14159 
14160  // throw an exception if test fails
14161  if (not success)
14162  {
14163  JSON_THROW(other_error::create(501, "unsuccessful: " + val.dump()));
14164  }
14165 
14166  break;
14167  }
14168 
14169  case patch_operations::invalid:
14170  {
14171  // op must be "add", "remove", "replace", "move", "copy", or
14172  // "test"
14173  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, "operation value '" + op + "' is invalid"));
14174  }
14175  }
14176  }
14177 
14178  return result;
14179  }
14180 
14213  static basic_json diff(const basic_json& source,
14214  const basic_json& target,
14215  const std::string& path = "")
14216  {
14217  // the patch
14218  basic_json result(value_t::array);
14219 
14220  // if the values are the same, return empty patch
14221  if (source == target)
14222  {
14223  return result;
14224  }
14225 
14226  if (source.type() != target.type())
14227  {
14228  // different types: replace value
14229  result.push_back(
14230  {
14231  {"op", "replace"},
14232  {"path", path},
14233  {"value", target}
14234  });
14235  }
14236  else
14237  {
14238  switch (source.type())
14239  {
14240  case value_t::array:
14241  {
14242  // first pass: traverse common elements
14243  size_t i = 0;
14244  while (i < source.size() and i < target.size())
14245  {
14246  // recursive call to compare array values at index i
14247  auto temp_diff = diff(source[i], target[i], path + "/" + std::to_string(i));
14248  result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
14249  ++i;
14250  }
14251 
14252  // i now reached the end of at least one array
14253  // in a second pass, traverse the remaining elements
14254 
14255  // remove my remaining elements
14256  const auto end_index = static_cast<difference_type>(result.size());
14257  while (i < source.size())
14258  {
14259  // add operations in reverse order to avoid invalid
14260  // indices
14261  result.insert(result.begin() + end_index, object(
14262  {
14263  {"op", "remove"},
14264  {"path", path + "/" + std::to_string(i)}
14265  }));
14266  ++i;
14267  }
14268 
14269  // add other remaining elements
14270  while (i < target.size())
14271  {
14272  result.push_back(
14273  {
14274  {"op", "add"},
14275  {"path", path + "/" + std::to_string(i)},
14276  {"value", target[i]}
14277  });
14278  ++i;
14279  }
14280 
14281  break;
14282  }
14283 
14284  case value_t::object:
14285  {
14286  // first pass: traverse this object's elements
14287  for (auto it = source.begin(); it != source.end(); ++it)
14288  {
14289  // escape the key name to be used in a JSON patch
14290  const auto key = json_pointer::escape(it.key());
14291 
14292  if (target.find(it.key()) != target.end())
14293  {
14294  // recursive call to compare object values at key it
14295  auto temp_diff = diff(it.value(), target[it.key()], path + "/" + key);
14296  result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
14297  }
14298  else
14299  {
14300  // found a key that is not in o -> remove it
14301  result.push_back(object(
14302  {
14303  {"op", "remove"},
14304  {"path", path + "/" + key}
14305  }));
14306  }
14307  }
14308 
14309  // second pass: traverse other object's elements
14310  for (auto it = target.begin(); it != target.end(); ++it)
14311  {
14312  if (source.find(it.key()) == source.end())
14313  {
14314  // found a key that is not in this -> add it
14315  const auto key = json_pointer::escape(it.key());
14316  result.push_back(
14317  {
14318  {"op", "add"},
14319  {"path", path + "/" + key},
14320  {"value", it.value()}
14321  });
14322  }
14323  }
14324 
14325  break;
14326  }
14327 
14328  default:
14329  {
14330  // both primitive type: replace value
14331  result.push_back(
14332  {
14333  {"op", "replace"},
14334  {"path", path},
14335  {"value", target}
14336  });
14337  break;
14338  }
14339  }
14340  }
14341 
14342  return result;
14343  }
14344 
14346 };
